1781977783725617	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzAw		item.create	bn-6pu	{"description":"Epic: deliver M0 (contracts, parser, manifests, canonicalization, evidence skeleton) plus the first vertical slice — the 14-op non-SDF touch-up loop from M0_DECISIONS.md (D1/D2). Exit when an agent can author, run, diagnose, and reproduce the 'agent edits blemish' conformance scenario end-to-end with a passing no-change-outside-mask assertion and a byte-identical rerun hash. Source: notes/paintop-plan/{plan.md M0/§25, IR_SPEC §20, OP_CATALOG §18, AGENT_VERIFICATION, M0_DECISIONS.md}. Defers GPU, Lua, models, GLB, tiling/cache (M2+), and the SDF mask calculus (M1.5).","kind":"goal","labels":["group-epic"],"size":"xl","title":"M0 + MVP non-SDF touch-up loop"}	blake3:sRUVALYwuoRS7O45K3_C1QONH_--74eYTa32jChA4iE
1781977984897456	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzBA		item.create	bn-tj0	{"description":"**What:** Create the root Cargo workspace and the crate skeletons needed for M0 + the MVP slice:\n`paintop-ir`, `paintop-image`, `paintop-core`, `paintop-cpu`, `paintop-testkit`, `paintop-cli`, `xtask`.\n(Defer `paintop-wgpu`, `paintop-model`, `paintop-material`, `paintop-msh-bridge` to later milestones — do NOT create them now.)\nSet `edition = \"2024\"`, add `rust-toolchain.toml` pinning a current **stable** channel with `rustfmt` + `clippy`\ncomponents, and declare the binding workspace lints. Wire `[lints] workspace = true` into every crate.\nEnforce the dependency direction from plan.md §6.1 (paintop-image must not know 3D exists; cpu impls contracts\nowned by ir/image/core; cli reuses canonical IR, no parallel structs).\n\n**Why:** Reproducible, strict foundation. The lint wall (below) is a hard quality gate the whole project relies on.\n\n**Binding root `Cargo.toml` (exact):**\n```toml\n[workspace.lints.rust]\nunsafe_code = \"forbid\"\n\n[workspace.lints.clippy]\npedantic = { level = \"deny\", priority = -1 }\nnursery  = { level = \"deny\", priority = -1 }\nunwrap_used = \"deny\"\n```\nAlso add a `clippy.toml` with `allow-unwrap-in-tests = true` and `allow-expect-in-tests = true` so test code may\nstill use `unwrap`/`expect`. See M0_DECISIONS.md D4.\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- Workspace builds: `cargo build --workspace` succeeds with all 7 crates present and empty/stub lib roots.\n- Every crate's `Cargo.toml` has `[lints] workspace = true`; root has the exact lint block above; `clippy.toml` present.\n- `rust-toolchain.toml` pins stable + rustfmt + clippy; `edition = \"2024\"` in every crate.\n- No `unsafe` anywhere (forbidden). No `anyhow` in any library crate (allowed only later in cli/xtask).\n- Dependency edges match §6.1 (e.g. `paintop-image` has no dep on any 3D/material crate).\n\n**Exit gate (must pass to close):**\n- `cargo build --workspace` → 0\n- `cargo fmt --check` → 0\n- `cargo clippy --workspace --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings` → 0 (with pedantic+nursery+unwrap_used denies active)\n\n**Testing strategy:** A trivial `#[test] fn smoke()` in one crate proving the test harness runs under the lint wall.\n**References:** plan.md §6, §6.1; M0_DECISIONS.md D4; ../msh Cargo.toml (edition 2024, serde 1.0, image 0.25, nalgebra 0.33).\n**Depends on:** (none — first bone)\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-bootstrap"],"parent":"bn-6pu","size":"m","title":"Scaffold Cargo workspace, crates, toolchain, and workspace lints"}	blake3:YlOeo6o2I5nUHhbaBnUpoqhAFOYAK0SYcZ-aBh7NzBs
1781977984998101	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzBQ		item.create	bn-3aj	{"description":"**What:** Add a `justfile` with `check` (runs fmt --check, clippy -D warnings, test, doc) and `install`.\nBuild the `xtask` binary skeleton with subcommand routing for `verify-op` and `fixture generate` (stubs that\nreturn a clean \"unimplemented\" error, not a panic). Add a per-PR CI workflow running the AGENT_VERIFICATION §2.1\nLayer-0 gates.\n\n**Why:** `just check` is the canonical pre-commit gate referenced by AGENTS.md and every later bone's exit gate.\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- `just check` runs and passes on the skeleton workspace (fmt, clippy -D warnings, `cargo test --workspace`, `cargo doc --workspace --no-deps`).\n- `cargo xtask --help` lists `verify-op` and `fixture` subcommands; invoking a stub returns a typed error + nonzero exit, never a panic.\n- CI config present and green on the Layer-0 gates (fmt/clippy/test/doc).\n\n**Exit gate (must pass to close):** `just check` → 0; `cargo xtask verify-op X` and `cargo xtask fixture generate Y` exit nonzero with a readable \"not yet implemented\" message (no panic, no unwrap).\n**Testing strategy:** Run `just check` in CI on a clean checkout.\n**References:** AGENT_VERIFICATION §2.1; AGENTS.md (just check / just install).\n**Depends on:** Scaffold Cargo workspace\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-bootstrap"],"parent":"bn-6pu","size":"s","title":"Add justfile, CI hygiene gates, and xtask command skeleton"}	blake3:OS8GxjdtvImMNN_vj4t1kbwjgDMc8G2WHVpnINzgCYI
1781977985106732	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzBg		item.create	bn-2i9	{"description":"**What:** Central error module in `paintop-ir`: a `class` enum (parse, schema, reference, type, semantic, policy,\nexecution, assertion, conformance, model, asset, export — IR_SPEC §19), stable `code` strings (e.g.\n`E_COLOR_ENCODING_MISMATCH`), structured context (`node`, `path`, `actual`, `expected`, `suggestions`),\nserialization to the exact §19 JSON shape, and the exit-code mapping from plan.md §15.4 (0/2/3/4/5/6/7/8/9).\nUse `thiserror` enums. No `anyhow` in this lib.\n\n**Why:** The structured error IS part of the agent-facing contract; every other bone emits these.\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- Each error class is constructible and carries structured context.\n- An error serializes to the exact §19 JSON shape (`{\"ok\":false,\"error\":{\"class\",\"code\",\"message\",\"node\",\"path\",\"actual\",\"expected\",\"suggestions\"}}`).\n- Exit-code mapping matches the §15.4 table exactly (unit-tested for every class).\n- No `.unwrap()`/`.expect()` in non-test code (satisfies `unwrap_used = \"deny\"`).\n\n**Exit gate (must pass to close):** `cargo test -p paintop-ir` includes a golden test of the §19 error JSON and a table test asserting class→exit-code for all 12 classes; `just check` → 0.\n**Testing strategy:** Golden JSON + exhaustive exit-code table test.\n**References:** IR_SPEC §19; plan.md §15.4; M0_DECISIONS.md D4 (thiserror + central taxonomy).\n**Depends on:** Scaffold Cargo workspace\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-ir"],"parent":"bn-6pu","size":"s","title":"Error taxonomy: stable classes, codes, and exit-code mapping"}	blake3:Jiq9aziCL6XzdSdjDiD6PhR1iKrFFtn_gkRUSLxWKJc
1781977985215184	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzBw		item.create	bn-1ve	{"description":"**What:** Rust types for resource descriptors (IR_SPEC §7): Image / Mask / Field1-3 / SdfMask descriptors and the\nenums they reference — color encoding (`srgb`, `linear-srgb`, `raw-linear`; `display-p3` and ICC are explicitly\n*rejected* for now), alpha representation (`premultiplied` / `straight`), scalar type (`u8`, `f32`, `u32`),\ncoordinate convention (`pixel-center-upper-left`), semantic role, and boundary modes (`constant`, `clamp`,\n`mirror`, `wrap`, `transparent`, `valid-only` — §8.4). An `Extent` type with **checked** arithmetic for pixel/byte\nmath, and a half-open `Rect` (`[x0,x1) × [y0,y1)`) per §8.1. Valid-range policy types (`bounded`/`unbounded`/\n`normalized-vector`) per §8.3. All `#[serde(deny_unknown_fields)]`.\n\n**Why:** Typed resources let the compiler reject nonsense (hue-rotating depth, sRGB-decoding a normal map). This is\nthe vocabulary every op and the parser build on.\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- Descriptor/enum types compile and serde round-trip with `deny_unknown_fields`.\n- Unknown enum variant → parse error (typed, from the error taxonomy).\n- `Extent` rejects overflowing pixel/byte products (checked arithmetic), tested at `u32::MAX`-ish boundaries.\n- `display-p3`/ICC encodings are representable-as-rejected (a decode requesting them yields a `semantic` error, not a silent fallback).\n- Coordinate convention (pixel center = (x+0.5,y+0.5), origin upper-left, half-open rects) documented in rustdoc per §8.1.\n\n**Exit gate (must pass to close):** `cargo test -p paintop-ir` covers enum-parse rejection + extent overflow + half-open rect math; `cargo doc` examples pass; `just check` → 0.\n**Testing strategy:** Unit + serde round-trip + doctest for the coordinate convention.\n**References:** IR_SPEC §7, §8.1, §8.3, §8.4; plan.md §4.5, §8.\n**Depends on:** Scaffold Cargo workspace; Error taxonomy\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-ir"],"parent":"bn-6pu","size":"m","title":"Resource metadata + coordinate/color/scalar/boundary enums"}	blake3:ANs4j2NcOvUrNpSsq2vdnASEB9C9faVH_IZgt1ClEto
1781977985321507	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzCA		item.create	bn-b3y	{"description":"**What:** The top-level plan document model (IR_SPEC §2: `paintop`, `name`, `description`, `policy`, `inputs`,\n`nodes`, `assertions`, `exports`, `evidence`, `extensions`) and node form (§5: `id`, `op`, single `in` object\n[D3 Q1], `params`, `hints`, `extensions`). A reference type that **always requires `/port`** (D3 Q2) — accepts\n`input:<id>` and `node:<id>/<port>`, rejects bare `node:<id>`. Implement parse pipeline phases 1–2 (plan.md §10.1):\nreject **duplicate JSON keys** (serde_json silently keeps the last — you MUST reject per §17 r12, via a\nduplicate-detecting deserializer or a raw-value prescan), enforce max document size and nesting depth BEFORE\nallocating large structures, reject JSON `NaN`/`Infinity` and fractional values for integer params (§10), and\nenforce the node-id regex `^[A-Za-z][A-Za-z0-9_.-]{0,127}$` (§3.1). All structs `deny_unknown_fields`.\n\n**Why:** \"Typos fail rather than silently change output.\" This is the strict front door the whole runtime depends on.\n\n**Acceptance criteria (each is a checked-in negative fixture that fails with the correct error class/code):**\n- valid minimal plan parses (`fixtures/plans/empty-valid.json`).\n- unknown top-level field → `schema`; unknown node field → `schema`.\n- duplicate key anywhere → `parse` (NOT last-wins).\n- `NaN`/`Infinity` literal → `parse`; fractional value for an integer param → `parse`/`type`.\n- oversize doc / over-deep nesting → rejected before large allocation.\n- bad node id (`../x`, `mask/x`, emoji) → `parse`.\n- bare reference `node:foo` without `/port` → `reference`; malformed reference → `reference`.\n\n**Exit gate (must pass to close):** `cargo test -p paintop-ir` parser suite covers every rejection case above with the exact error class; the valid fixture round-trips; `just check` → 0. (CLI surface wired in the CLI bone.)\n**Testing strategy:** Table-driven negative fixtures + one positive fixture; property test that random unknown fields always reject.\n**References:** IR_SPEC §2, §3.1, §3.2, §5, §10; §17 r12; plan.md §10.1; M0_DECISIONS.md D3 (Q1 single `in`, Q2 always `/port`).\n**Depends on:** Resource metadata enums; Error taxonomy\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-ir"],"parent":"bn-6pu","size":"l","title":"Strict plan parser: deny-unknown-fields, duplicate-key + size/depth rejection"}	blake3:vYnGYj696pWm0aS-zxM4IcU9iGnqqPSUlf19ayMm2ao
1781977985430839	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzCQ		item.create	bn-31z	{"description":"**What:** `OpManifest` types (plan.md §9): stable id + semantic major, input/output ports & resource types,\nparameter schema + defaults, semantics block (purity, color_requirement, alpha_requirement, roi, halo,\ndeterminism tier, seed requirement), available implementations, mathematical properties, limits, reference\nfixture ids. A registry keyed by `namespace.name@major` that rejects duplicate ids and dangling implementation\nrefs. The `OpContract` trait (IR_SPEC §18: `infer_outputs`, `required_inputs`, `validate_postconditions`).\nA manifest↔Rust-impl agreement check (ports and defaults must match). Generate `schemas/op-manifest-v1.schema.json`.\n\n**Why:** Manifests drive validation, scheduling, testing, and agent introspection (`op list`/`op schema`). Every\nop bone registers one.\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- A sample manifest loads and validates against the generated JSON Schema.\n- Registry rejects duplicate op ids and unknown implementation references with typed errors.\n- `OpContract` is object-safe and implemented by a stub op; a test asserts manifest ports == stub impl ports/defaults.\n- `infer_outputs`/`required_inputs`/`validate_postconditions` are deterministic and cheap (documented contract, IR_SPEC §18).\n\n**Exit gate (must pass to close):** `cargo test` manifest/registry/contract suite passes; `schemas/op-manifest-v1.schema.json` is generated and checked in; `just check` → 0.\n**Testing strategy:** Unit tests for registry invariants + a manifest/impl agreement test for a stub op.\n**References:** plan.md §9, §24; IR_SPEC §18; OP_CATALOG §19.\n**Depends on:** Resource metadata enums; Error taxonomy\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-ir"],"parent":"bn-6pu","size":"l","title":"Operation manifest model, registry, OpContract trait, and schema export"}	blake3:HlmO9CKc0ydvc2S7kUWOEoXkatiIB70iLdHJttRJPKY
1781977985539945	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzCg		item.create	bn-1e0	{"description":"**What:** A canonical-bytes serializer implementing all of IR_SPEC §17: resolve defaults, resolve seeds, expand\nsugar (none yet), emit canonical op ids with major version, **lexicographically sort object keys**, preserve\nsemantic array order, normalize unit-bearing values to canonical units, normalize references, normalize\nboundary/color/alpha/coordinate descriptors, strip non-semantic `description`/comments from the semantic hash,\nrepresent floats with a **single round-trippable format**, reject duplicate keys (reuse parser), include\nextensions in the hash only when their namespace declares semantic impact. Emit both `normalized-plan.json`\n(readable, stable) and a `semantic-hash` (`blake3:…`). Exclude compiler/runtime version from the semantic hash;\ninclude op semantic versions. Provide a hashing helper that emits algorithm-prefixed strings (`blake3:` internal,\n`sha256:` for interop) per M0_DECISIONS.md D4. **Never hash raw serde_json output.**\n\n**Why:** Canonicalization underpins reproducibility, caching, replay, and meaningful diffs — the project's core bet.\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- Reordering keys / changing whitespace / editing the non-semantic `description` → **identical** semantic hash.\n- Any semantic param change → **different** semantic hash.\n- `normalized-plan.json` re-parses to a plan whose semantic hash is identical (AGENT_VERIFICATION §2.4 property).\n- Float canonical form is stable and round-trips; negative zero normalized where semantics don't distinguish it.\n- Hash strings are algorithm-prefixed; BLAKE3 used for the semantic hash.\n\n**Exit gate (must pass to close):** property tests \"serialize→reparse preserves semantic hash\", \"non-semantic edits don't change hash\", and \"semantic edits do change hash\" all pass; `just check` → 0.\n**Testing strategy:** proptest over small plans with semantics-preserving vs semantics-changing mutations.\n**References:** IR_SPEC §17, §2.4; plan.md §10.3; M0_DECISIONS.md D4.\n**Depends on:** Strict plan parser; Resource metadata enums\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-ir"],"parent":"bn-6pu","size":"l","title":"Canonicalization + BLAKE3 semantic hashing module"}	blake3:Ffycxp-bp-B4gelujcX6csrbEFxkmD4a-oF0HWNI2ic
1781977985653133	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzCw		item.create	bn-yjj	{"description":"**What:** `cargo xtask fixture generate <kind> …` producing versioned analytic fixtures from fixed formulas\n(AGENT_VERIFICATION §2.3, §4.3): constant, single impulse, horizontal/vertical ramp, checkerboard, sine grating,\nbinary rectangle/circle, alpha-edge-with-hidden-RGB, tiny images (1×1, 1×N, 2×2), NaN/Inf-injected field, large-ID\nlabel map. Output each as an **exact numeric array** (JSON or binary, not a quantized screenshot) plus a preview\nPNG and a fixture manifest recording formula, params, version, and sha256.\n\n**Why:** Analytic fixtures let agents derive expected behavior instead of trusting a render. Every op bone tests\nagainst these.\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- Each fixture kind generates **deterministically** (byte-identical across runs and machines).\n- Manifest records formula name + params + version + sha256 (AGENT_VERIFICATION §4.2 shape).\n- Arrays are exact-precision; preview PNG is auxiliary, never the source of truth.\n\n**Exit gate (must pass to close):** `cargo xtask fixture generate impulse --width 65 --height 65 --x 32 --y 32 --format f32 --out <path>` produces a file whose sha256 matches a checked-in expected; re-running yields byte-identical output; `just check` → 0.\n**Testing strategy:** Hash-stability test per fixture kind; one regeneration-determinism test.\n**References:** AGENT_VERIFICATION §2.3, §4.2, §4.3.\n**Depends on:** justfile + xtask skeleton; Resource metadata enums\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-evidence"],"parent":"bn-6pu","size":"m","title":"Analytic fixture generator (xtask + paintop-testkit)"}	blake3:8yhCDtbPcm6vqdIhso38arxhhmnF-j2h8h1M8VUe1n0
1781977985764868	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzDA		item.create	bn-2ek	{"description":"**What:** An evidence-bundle writer (plan.md §15.1, AGENT_VERIFICATION §5): `manifest.json` (runtime+gitsha,\n`plan_semantic_hash`, platform, determinism tier, status, exit_code, outputs, failures — timestamps are provenance,\nexcluded from semantic identity), `normalized-plan.json`, `trace.jsonl` (JSON Lines; event types from §5.2 with\nstable keys + a schema version), `metrics.json`, `assertions.json`, and `outputs/ intermediates/ masks/ diffs/\nlogs/` plus `contact-sheet.png`. **Atomic writes** (temp-then-rename). A failure-driven materialization hook\n(plan.md §18.2) and a minimal-replay emitter stub (§5.4). A contact-sheet compositor (before/after/diff).\n\n**Why:** Evidence is how agents diagnose and trust runs. Required by the conformance exit gate.\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- A run with `--bundle DIR` emits the full directory structure; missing optional artifacts are simply absent, not malformed.\n- `trace.jsonl` lines validate against the event schema; every event has a schema version + stable keys.\n- `manifest.json` excludes wall-clock time from semantic identity (provenance only).\n- Writes are atomic (temp file then rename); a crash mid-write leaves no partial canonical artifact.\n- A failed/empty run still produces a valid `manifest.json` carrying the correct `exit_code` and `failures`.\n\n**Exit gate (must pass to close):** integration test runs a trivial plan, asserts bundle structure + manifest fields + trace schema; the assertion-failure path additionally produces `assertions.json` + a minimal replay file; `just check` → 0.\n**Testing strategy:** Integration test over the executor (once available) + JSON-schema validation of trace/manifest.\n**References:** plan.md §15.1, §18.2; AGENT_VERIFICATION §5.\n**Depends on:** Canonicalization + BLAKE3 hashing; Error taxonomy\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-evidence"],"parent":"bn-6pu","size":"l","title":"Evidence bundle writer + structured trace skeleton"}	blake3:7MbBHGq6m0Zz0U2BgIfwc30oCs3VGEY1DNiouhv11fE
1781977985876621	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzDQ		item.create	bn-kfw	{"description":"**What:** The minimal compile+execute spine for the MVP (subset of plan.md §10.1 phases 3,4,7,11 — NO tiling,\nNO cache; those are M2). Reference resolution (resolve `input:`/`node:.../port`, detect cycles and missing refs),\ntype/shape/color/alpha checking via `OpContract::infer_outputs` (reject color/alpha mismatches with stable codes,\ne.g. a linear-only op fed sRGB → `E_COLOR_ENCODING_MISMATCH`), backward demand from exports+assertions with basic\ndead-node elimination, and a **whole-image sequential executor** that runs nodes in topological order invoking each\nop's `cpu.reference` implementation. Emit per-node trace events into the evidence bundle.\n\n**Why:** This is the spine every MVP op plugs into and the thing the conformance scenario runs through.\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- A multi-node plan resolves and executes in topological order; outputs are correct for a synthetic stub graph.\n- Cycle → `reference` error; missing/dangling ref → `reference` error.\n- Color/alpha mismatch → `semantic`/`type` error with the right code (proves the type checker bites).\n- A node not demanded by any export/assertion is eliminated and never executed (assert via trace).\n- Each executed node emits a trace event (op id, impl, regions, elapsed, cache=miss/n-a).\n\n**Exit gate (must pass to close):** integration test runs a ≥3-node synthetic plan end-to-end through the executor with trace assertions; dead-node + cycle + color-mismatch cases tested; `just check` → 0.\n**Testing strategy:** Integration tests with stub ops registered in the registry; trace inspection.\n**References:** plan.md §10.1 (phases 3,4,7,11), §10.2; IR_SPEC §18; M0_DECISIONS.md D2.\n**Depends on:** Operation manifest model + registry; Canonicalization + BLAKE3 hashing; Evidence bundle writer; Error taxonomy\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-ops"],"parent":"bn-6pu","size":"l","title":"Graph resolver + type/color/alpha checker + sequential whole-image executor"}	blake3:2YF8TJ2tBmP_23WATEknztVbWsSuUgwFUEUWrWPSeLw
1781977985987614	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzDg		item.create	bn-c5d	{"description":"**What:** Implement `cargo xtask verify-op <op-id>` (AGENT_VERIFICATION §14): locate+validate the manifest, run\nits schema examples, run op-tagged unit/analytic/property/metamorphic/differential and smoke-bench categories\n(ROI/tile/cache categories are declared \"N/A until M2\" with a reason), then emit\n`target/verification/<op-id>/{index.json,summary.md,test-results.json,differential/,properties/,benchmarks/,contact-sheet.png}`.\nFail if any *applicable* required category is missing; \"N/A\" requires a manifest-declared reason.\n\n**Why:** This command is the *exit gate* of every op bone — it operationalizes plan.md §24's definition of done.\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- `cargo xtask verify-op <id>` produces the report directory and a machine-readable `index.json`.\n- Missing an applicable required category → non-zero exit + a clear message naming the gap.\n- A manifest declaring a category \"N/A\" without a reason → failure.\n- Wired into CI's changed-op job.\n\n**Exit gate (must pass to close):** `cargo xtask verify-op <first available op>` produces a passing report dir; a deliberately-incomplete op fails with the missing-category message; `just check` → 0.\n**Testing strategy:** Run against the first real op (color.convert) plus a synthetic incomplete op.\n**References:** AGENT_VERIFICATION §14, §15, §6; plan.md §24.\n**Depends on:** Operation manifest model + registry; Analytic fixture generator; Graph resolver + executor\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-ops"],"parent":"bn-6pu","size":"l","title":"verify-op runner: automated per-operation definition-of-done"}	blake3:wEBzRM-ULFoKIYkYmJrbySxZ1nQ6r1coBY803F4AMsQ
1781977986094927	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzDw		item.create	bn-1ez	{"description":"**What:** PNG decode → `Image` and `Image` → PNG export, behind enforced decode limits (plan.md §17.2: max\ndecoded pixels/dimensions, integer-overflow checks, reject truncated/malformed, decompression-bomb guard),\npreserving color encoding + alpha representation metadata. Encode is lossless with an atomic write and a documented\ndeterministic contract. Uses the `image` crate (0.25) for codecs only — convert into `paintop` resource types\nimmediately. Register manifests + `OpContract`s for both ops.\n\n**Acceptance criteria:** decode∘encode round-trip within the lossless contract; alpha/color metadata preserved; truncated/oversize/bomb inputs rejected with `asset`/`policy` codes; no `unsafe`.\n**Exit gate (must pass to close):** `cargo xtask verify-op io.decode_image@1` and `verify-op io.encode_image@1` both pass (manifest, schema example, analytic round-trip, differential vs known decoder test vectors, fuzz seed corpus of malformed PNGs); `just check` → 0.\n**Testing strategy:** Round-trip property; malformed-PNG fuzz seeds; metadata-preservation goldens.\n**References:** OP_CATALOG §1; plan.md §17.2; AGENT_VERIFICATION §2.9.\n**Depends on:** Graph resolver + executor; verify-op runner; Analytic fixture generator\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-ops"],"parent":"bn-6pu","size":"m","title":"Op: io.decode_image@1 + io.encode_image@1 (PNG, hardened, round-trip)"}	blake3:BUmEjP3dIjwCgxFHSny1hx9ULDY9hQQFewoGYJj-Mkc
1781977986202297	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzEA		item.create	bn-1b1	{"description":"**What:** Transfer-function decode/encode between `srgb` and `linear-srgb` (plan.md §8.2) with explicit\nsource/destination encodings; reject unsupported targets (`display-p3` without a backend, ICC) and `raw-linear`↔\ncolor misuse. CPU reference semantics.\n**Acceptance criteria:** encode∘decode round-trip within tolerance; matches a known sRGB↔linear value table (analytic); monotonic; rejects misuse with `semantic` errors.\n**Exit gate (must pass to close):** `cargo xtask verify-op color.convert@1` passes (analytic value table, round-trip metamorphic, monotonicity property, rejection tests); `just check` → 0.\n**Testing strategy:** Analytic value table + round-trip + rejection cases.\n**References:** OP_CATALOG §2; plan.md §8.2; AGENT_VERIFICATION §2.5.\n**Depends on:** Graph resolver + executor; verify-op runner; Analytic fixture generator\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-ops"],"parent":"bn-6pu","size":"s","title":"Op: color.convert@1 (sRGB ↔ linear-srgb)"}	blake3:GGDmGdFkEd11EVVspZ8OPUlXJMdg2siEHEOArMKM53g
1781977986313022	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzEQ		item.create	bn-242	{"description":"**What:** Premultiply/unpremultiply in linear light (plan.md §8.2). Reject premultiply on nonlinear-encoded RGB\n(§8 rule). Unpremultiply uses an explicit epsilon/policy for near-zero alpha. Preserve hidden-RGB semantics; never\nsilently discard transparent color.\n**Acceptance criteria:** round-trip for alpha>epsilon (metamorphic §2.5); the alpha-edge-with-hidden-RGB fixture exports with **no colored fringe** (§3.2); premultiply on sRGB rejected; output alpha/color in range.\n**Exit gate (must pass to close):** `cargo xtask verify-op alpha.premultiply@1` and `verify-op alpha.unpremultiply@1` pass (round-trip metamorphic, hidden-RGB fringe fixture, rejection test); `just check` → 0.\n**Testing strategy:** Round-trip property + hidden-RGB fringe golden + rejection.\n**References:** OP_CATALOG §2; plan.md §8.2; AGENT_VERIFICATION §3.2.\n**Depends on:** Graph resolver + executor; verify-op runner; Analytic fixture generator\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-ops"],"parent":"bn-6pu","size":"s","title":"Op: alpha.premultiply@1 + alpha.unpremultiply@1"}	blake3:NEIFbCXrYkQ2t4I4mLtfAgO3H-nTu1TGzi4cGr8r9pA
1781977986417469	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzEg		item.create	bn-2z8	{"description":"**What (KEY MVP op — M0_DECISIONS.md D1):** Analytic ellipse coverage with rotation (`angle_rad`),\n`antialias: analytic`, `extent_from` an input, producing a `Mask` in [0,1]. Add the new\n`edge: { profile: smoothstep, half_width_px: N }` parameter that feathers the edge **analytically** from the\nellipse's implicit quadratic — this replaces the SDF chain for the first slice and gives \"feather by a physical\npixel radius\" with zero distance-field infrastructure.\n**Acceptance criteria:** rendered coverage matches analytic geometry (area converges with resolution, §3.6); 90° rotation/reflection covariance; the soft-edge transition width equals `half_width_px` in physical pixels (measured property); half-open pixel convention holds on pixel-aligned cases; degenerate radii rejected; no NaN.\n**Exit gate (must pass to close):** `cargo xtask verify-op mask.ellipse@1` passes (analytic area convergence, rotation covariance, feather-width property, half-open-convention fixture, degenerate rejection, translation metamorphic); `just check` → 0.\n**Testing strategy:** Analytic area/feather properties + rotation/translation metamorphic + degenerate rejection.\n**References:** OP_CATALOG §3; AGENT_VERIFICATION §3.6; M0_DECISIONS.md D1; IR_SPEC §20 (rewritten example).\n**Depends on:** Graph resolver + executor; verify-op runner; Analytic fixture generator\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-ops"],"parent":"bn-6pu","size":"m","title":"Op: mask.ellipse@1 with analytic soft-edge feather"}	blake3:Zk_way8297XHmimYrH7DAEEG9vYNhZVlyCLqsgyFIk8
1781977986528686	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzEw		item.create	bn-1oa	{"description":"**What:** Anisotropic Gaussian splats, CPU reference (AGENT_VERIFICATION §3.5; IR_SPEC §11). Each splat: center,\ncovariance from `sigma_px` + `angle_rad`, `opacity`, `blend` (at least `multiply` and `normal`). Bounded support\ntruncation with a **reported tail-energy bound**. Batch limit enforced from `policy.resources.max_splats`. Splat\nbatch is **inline in `params`** (D3 Q6). Paints onto `base` producing an **edit-layer** `Image` — NO `clip` in the\nMVP; authorization is delegated to `composite.masked_replace` (M0_DECISIONS.md D2). Linear-srgb space.\n**Acceptance criteria:** center symmetry; covariance axes align with specified rotation; translation covariance; zero-opacity identity; split-batch equivalence for commutative blend modes; truncated-Gaussian mass bound reported and within budget; finite output.\n**Exit gate (must pass to close):** `cargo xtask verify-op paint.gaussian_splats@1` passes (center/axis analytic samples, covariance reconstruction from weighted moments, 90° rotation covariance, translation metamorphic, split-batch equivalence, truncation-mass bound); `just check` → 0.\n**Testing strategy:** Analytic + metamorphic + split-batch decomposition per §3.5.\n**References:** OP_CATALOG §6; AGENT_VERIFICATION §3.5; IR_SPEC §11; M0_DECISIONS.md D2/D3-Q6.\n**Depends on:** Graph resolver + executor; verify-op runner; Analytic fixture generator\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-ops"],"parent":"bn-6pu","size":"l","title":"Op: paint.gaussian_splats@1 (CPU reference, edit-layer, inline batch)"}	blake3:1uc4IEZ6kaKdHJYezAIzTPFW28H49ZtNbn2wXoztqZ8
1781977986638457	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzFA		item.create	bn-2lp	{"description":"**What:** Pointwise color adjustments in linear light (AGENT_VERIFICATION §3.1): explicit `exposure_ev`,\n`saturation`, `temperature` sub-parameters; an optional `mask` input (unused in the MVP graph but supported).\n`exposure(x,e) = x·2^e`. CPU reference.\n**Acceptance criteria:** empty-mask identity; full-mask == unmasked; exposure composition before clamp (`E_a∘E_b = E_{a+b}` in unclamped linear); zero-adjustment identity; monotonic for exposure/gamma over nonnegative domain; finite; no change outside mask at reference precision.\n**Exit gate (must pass to close):** `cargo xtask verify-op color.adjust@1` passes (the §3.1 property set incl. exposure composition + masked identity); `just check` → 0.\n**Testing strategy:** Property tests from §3.1; HDR / alpha-zero adversarial fixtures.\n**References:** OP_CATALOG §2; AGENT_VERIFICATION §3.1.\n**Depends on:** Graph resolver + executor; verify-op runner; Analytic fixture generator\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-ops"],"parent":"bn-6pu","size":"s","title":"Op: color.adjust@1 (linear-light exposure/saturation/temperature, optional mask)"}	blake3:ezsofnzeVj17hYg2qRD1SovrZFPNIoY8Kz4Ca62bGUU
1781977986749584	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzFQ		item.create	bn-1x2	{"description":"**What:** `out = m·edited + (1−m)·base` in premultiplied linear light (IR_SPEC §9.1). This is the **single MVP\nauthorization boundary** (M0_DECISIONS.md D2) — the one place locality is enforced, and exactly what\n`assert.no_change_outside_mask` verifies against.\n**Acceptance criteria:** `m=0` → output is `base` bit-exactly; `m=1` → output is `edited` bit-exactly; wherever `m=0`, output is **bit-identical to base** (reference precision); premultiplied-correct compositing; finite.\n**Exit gate (must pass to close):** `cargo xtask verify-op composite.masked_replace@1` passes (m∈{0,1} exactness, outside-region bit-identity, premultiplied correctness, soft-mask blend property); `just check` → 0.\n**Testing strategy:** Exactness at mask extremes + outside-region identity property (the safety-critical one).\n**References:** OP_CATALOG §7; IR_SPEC §9.1; M0_DECISIONS.md D2.\n**Depends on:** Graph resolver + executor; verify-op runner; Analytic fixture generator\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-ops"],"parent":"bn-6pu","size":"s","title":"Op: composite.masked_replace@1 (the authorization primitive)"}	blake3:pf7M7rzdg-fqamQqrBseOHnTzB8INL0iXbNfuxoXIjI
1781977986859442	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzFg		item.create	bn-1fe	{"description":"**What:** `Image` → `Report` carrying extent, per-channel ranges, finite-value stats, and a content hash\n(OP_CATALOG §1). Exercises the `Report` resource type early; used by the agent to author the first plan.\n**Acceptance criteria:** report fields correct on analytic fixtures (constant → known stats; NaN-injected → nonfinite flagged); content hash stable and matches the hashing module; pure (no mutation).\n**Exit gate (must pass to close):** `cargo xtask verify-op image.inspect@1` passes (stats correctness on constant/ramp/NaN fixtures, hash stability); `just check` → 0.\n**Testing strategy:** Analytic-fixture stat checks + hash stability.\n**References:** OP_CATALOG §1; M0_DECISIONS.md D2 (image.inspect included).\n**Depends on:** Graph resolver + executor; verify-op runner; Analytic fixture generator\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-ops"],"parent":"bn-6pu","size":"s","title":"Op: image.inspect@1 → Report"}	blake3:Fx7_5T5whU9r1cngYNB9BfSJGFsblFeKgIKqHkUm9vM
1781977986965263	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzFw		item.create	bn-1kx	{"description":"**What:** `before` + `after` → diff fields + a report (max/mean/RMS error, changed bounds), with an explicit\n`comparison_space` (OP_CATALOG §12). Produces a heatmap output consumed by the evidence bundle's `diffs/`.\n**Acceptance criteria:** identical inputs → zero diff + empty changed-bounds; a known injected delta → exact metrics; comparison space honored (linear vs encoded); finite.\n**Exit gate (must pass to close):** `cargo xtask verify-op analyze.diff@1` passes (zero-diff identity, known-delta exact metrics, comparison-space test); `just check` → 0.\n**Testing strategy:** Identity + known-delta analytic checks.\n**References:** OP_CATALOG §12; plan.md §25 (diff artifact).\n**Depends on:** Graph resolver + executor; verify-op runner; Analytic fixture generator\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-ops"],"parent":"bn-6pu","size":"s","title":"Op: analyze.diff@1 → diff fields + report"}	blake3:lLGjuqJEvToyj-lLoOeWo0G79CjfVs66DJVdS6BpUPw
1781977987072435	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzGA		item.create	bn-21z	{"description":"**What:** The two MVP assertions (IR_SPEC §13, OP_CATALOG §12), implemented as ordinary typed nodes that\nparticipate in graph demand. `assert.no_change_outside_mask(before, after, allowed)` with `comparison_space`,\n`outside_threshold`, `coverage_epsilon` → `Report` + pass/fail mapping to **exit class 6**; on failure it writes\nan outside-diff artifact + worst-pixel (AGENT_VERIFICATION §5.3) and a minimal replay. `assert.finite(resource)`\n→ locations of any NaN/Inf. Severity model (`error`/`warning`/`metric`) per §13.\n**Acceptance criteria:** a localized edit passes; an edit leaking 1 pixel outside the mask **fails** with worst-pixel + outside-diff artifact + exit code 6; NaN-injected resource → `assert.finite` fails with locations; `metric` severity never fails the run.\n**Exit gate (must pass to close):** `cargo xtask verify-op assert.no_change_outside_mask@1` and `verify-op assert.finite@1` pass (pass case, leak-fail case with artifact + exit 6, finite-fail case, severity behavior); `just check` → 0.\n**Testing strategy:** Synthetic localized vs leaking edits; NaN injection; severity matrix.\n**References:** IR_SPEC §13; OP_CATALOG §12; AGENT_VERIFICATION §5.3; plan.md §15.4 (exit code 6).\n**Depends on:** Graph resolver + executor; verify-op runner; Analytic fixture generator; Evidence bundle writer\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-ops"],"parent":"bn-6pu","size":"m","title":"Op: assert.no_change_outside_mask@1 + assert.finite@1"}	blake3:AvA-vzmXCZXHUY5bCPUaQBSCjuj78-tzch2HeTJwgto
1781977987186607	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzGQ		item.create	bn-1f4	{"description":"**What:** `resource` → identical `resource` + an evidence artifact written to the bundle; a materialization\nbarrier that must NOT change semantics (OP_CATALOG §1).\n**Acceptance criteria:** output is bit-identical to input (no semantic change); the artifact is written to `intermediates/`; the node participates in demand (forces materialization) without altering downstream hashes.\n**Exit gate (must pass to close):** `cargo xtask verify-op debug.materialize@1` passes (identity property + artifact-written check + downstream-hash-unchanged); `just check` → 0.\n**Testing strategy:** Identity property + bundle artifact assertion.\n**References:** OP_CATALOG §1; plan.md §4.6, §18.\n**Depends on:** Graph resolver + executor; verify-op runner; Evidence bundle writer\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-ops"],"parent":"bn-6pu","size":"xs","title":"Op: debug.materialize@1 (semantics-preserving evidence barrier)"}	blake3:Q5CAkj1f0pBqz1k-I2pYdBkVIUGKBxA7fJlTVKCJ0UM
1781977987298986	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzGg		item.create	bn-ajx	{"description":"**What:** A `clap`-based CLI (`paintop-cli`) per plan.md §15.4: subcommands `validate`, `run --bundle`,\n`explain --format json`, `graph --out`, `diff`, `op list`, `op schema <id>`, and a `selftest` stub. **stdout is\npure machine-readable JSON in machine modes; all logs go to stderr.** Stable exit classes from §15.4. Reuse the\ncanonical IR types — no parallel CLI structs (§6.1).\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- `paintop validate fixtures/plans/empty-valid.json` → exit 0.\n- `paintop validate fixtures/plans/unknown-field.json` → exit 2 with a stable error code (M0 exit criterion).\n- `paintop op list --format json` and `paintop op schema <id>` emit valid JSON.\n- stdout in machine mode is pure JSON (no log lines); exit classes match §15.4 (0/2/3/4/5/6/7/8/9).\n**Exit gate (must pass to close):** the two `validate` commands return the documented exit codes; `op list`/`op schema` produce valid JSON; a test asserts stdout/stderr separation; `just check` → 0.\n**Testing strategy:** CLI integration tests asserting exit codes + stdout-is-JSON.\n**References:** plan.md §15.4, §6.1; IR_SPEC §19; M0 exit criteria (plan.md §19).\n**Depends on:** Strict plan parser; Operation manifest model + registry; Canonicalization + BLAKE3 hashing; Graph resolver + executor\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-conformance"],"parent":"bn-6pu","size":"m","title":"paintop CLI: validate / run / explain / graph / diff / op list / op schema"}	blake3:VPHvl-j-Vu0oB62MaylrPnrTJFgGI8zT8k-xBIJgwog
1781977987410601	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzGw		item.create	bn-3v7	{"description":"**What (THE epic exit gate):** Check in the full rewritten §25 / IR_SPEC §20 scenario as a conformance plan +\nfixtures + tolerance profiles under `conformance/`. The plan runs the 14-op non-SDF loop: decode → inspect →\nsoft-ellipse mask → splats on edit layer → color.adjust → composite.masked_replace through the authorized mask →\nassert no change outside mask → encode, emitting a full evidence bundle (output, mask, diff, contact sheet,\nnormalized plan, trace). Then **rerun and verify an identical CPU-reference content hash** (reproducibility).\nInclude a deliberately-leaking variant that MUST fail with exit code 6 + a minimal replay.\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- `paintop run conformance/plans/blemish.json --bundle run/` → exit 0; the `no_change_outside_mask` assertion passes; the evidence bundle is complete.\n- A second run produces a **byte-identical** semantic hash AND identical output content hash.\n- The leaking variant → exit 6 with `assertions.json` + a minimal replay reproducing the failure.\n- The scenario is documented so a low-context agent can reproduce it from the README.\n**Exit gate (must pass to close):** all four acceptance bullets verified in CI (a `conformance` job); `just check` → 0.\n**Testing strategy:** Full end-to-end run + reproducibility rerun + negative leaking variant, all in CI.\n**References:** plan.md §25 (rewritten), §3.1; IR_SPEC §20 (rewritten); AGENT_VERIFICATION §5; M0_DECISIONS.md D1/D2.\n**Depends on:** ALL op bones; paintop CLI; Evidence bundle writer\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-conformance"],"parent":"bn-6pu","size":"m","title":"End-to-end conformance: 'agent edits blemish' (non-SDF MVP loop)"}	blake3:Np7BcWFGUmrUzUNQVRBlYoOzwnyhg4KGvz9P6zOAvZY
1781977987530987	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzHA		item.create	bn-3bj	{"description":"**What:** Wire the plan.md §19 M0 exit criteria into CI as a gate, and confirm the M1 \"all operations have\nmanifests\" criterion holds for the MVP ops. Write a short `docs/` + README \"how to run the loop\" plus the agent\ncompletion-report template (AGENT_VERIFICATION §6.1). Final tidy: ensure all MVP ops register manifests and pass\nverify-op.\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- CI M0 gate is green and runs: `cargo fmt --check`; `cargo clippy --workspace --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings` (pedantic+nursery+unwrap denies); `cargo test --workspace`; `paintop validate fixtures/plans/empty-valid.json` (0); `paintop validate fixtures/plans/unknown-field.json` (fails predictably).\n- Every MVP op has a manifest; `op list` shows all 14; each passes `verify-op`.\n- A fresh-clone walkthrough (`just check` → run the conformance loop) is documented and verified.\n- The M0 + first-half-M1 exit-criteria checklist is ticked with evidence paths.\n**Exit gate (must pass to close):** the CI M0 gate passes on a clean checkout; the documented fresh-clone walkthrough works end-to-end; `just check` → 0.\n**Testing strategy:** CI gate + a documented manual fresh-clone smoke.\n**References:** plan.md §19 (M0 + M1 exit criteria); AGENT_VERIFICATION §2.1, §6.1.\n**Depends on:** paintop CLI; verify-op runner; End-to-end conformance\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-conformance"],"parent":"bn-6pu","size":"s","title":"M0 exit-criteria CI gate + agent docs"}	blake3:G7EEzraV273l5HHQ6bsCN3LjJ0UjUJA9qcvj64Jv6D4
