1781978407272451	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzRg		item.create	bn-1kr	{"description":"Finish the P0 stable operation set (OP_CATALOG §18) beyond the MVP 14: remaining primitive masks + boolean algebra, image.create/crop/pad/resize, fill+gradients, composite.over/blend, direct convolution + reference Gaussian blur, statistics/histogram/changed_bounds, and the remaining range/alpha/bounds assertions, plus the Field1 type. Exit (plan.md §19 M1): every P0 op has a manifest + passing verify-op; analytic/property tests pass; an agent completes a fixture edit using only CLI introspection + evidence. Source: notes/paintop-plan/{plan.md M1, OP_CATALOG §18, AGENT_VERIFICATION §3}.","kind":"goal","labels":["group-m1"],"size":"xl","title":"M1 — exact 2D CPU core (finish P0)"}	blake3:UmHrq720Mpk3R__69DbNTs3OW0RLV81vYmPzxOoESNU
1781978407420531	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzRw		item.create	bn-9oi	{"description":"Land the deferred signed-distance mask calculus immediately after the MVP loop is green (M0_DECISIONS.md D1): exact Euclidean distance transform (Felzenszwalb–Huttenlocher) with a brute-force oracle, mask.to_sdf/sdf.to_mask/sdf.offset, SDF boolean ops, the grow/shrink/feather macros that normalize to SDF, and mask topology (connected components / fill holes / remove small) with a LabelMap type. Exit: the original SDF north-star variant (mask.to_sdf→sdf.offset→sdf.to_mask) runs end-to-end; EDT brute-force differential + offset-composition + boolean SDF laws verified. Source: OP_CATALOG §4, ALIEN_OPS §2, RESEARCH §3.1.","kind":"goal","labels":["group-m15"],"size":"xl","title":"M1.5 — exact EDT + SDF mask calculus"}	blake3:wszMrVrlFe7ug0zcZl3HCfd1PpBmme93C7v-Jb1ILrA
1781978407571117	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzSA		item.create	bn-97e	{"description":"Turn the sequential whole-image executor into a demand-driven tiled compiler (plan.md §19 M2, §11): backward ROI/halo propagation, tile scheduler + sparse mask tile summaries, deterministic reductions, content-addressed BLAKE3 cache, graph simplification (constant folding / identity elimination / CSE / conversion cancellation), and graph visualization. Exit: whole-image == tiled for exact ops; ROI differentially equivalent to full; a small masked 4K edit touches only predicted tiles; cache replay performs zero unnecessary execution. Source: plan.md §10.1, §11, §10.3.","kind":"goal","labels":["group-m2"],"size":"xl","title":"M2 — graph compiler, tiles, ROI, and cache"}	blake3:fY4hEXM6vBvmgBGDkpdVpFSm0lUxNFcvRr1GI-aFR9M
1781978495149537	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzSQ		item.create	bn-34g	{"description":"**What:** Add the typed `Field1` (scalar field) resource and two ops: `image.extract_channel@1`\n(`Image` → `Field1`/`Mask`, channel semantics explicit) and `image.assemble_channels@1` (fields → `Image`,\nshape/range/channel mapping validated). `Field1` is an M1 deliverable and the substrate for convolution on scalar\ndata and for distance fields in M1.5.\n**Acceptance:** Field1 round-trips with `deny_unknown_fields`; extract→assemble round-trips a multi-channel image; channel/range mismatch rejected with typed errors; assemble rejects extent mismatch.\n**Exit gate:** `cargo xtask verify-op image.extract_channel@1` and `verify-op image.assemble_channels@1` pass (round-trip metamorphic, mismatch rejection); `just check` → 0.\n**Refs:** OP_CATALOG §1; plan.md §7.1 (Field1), §19 M1.\n**Depends on:** verify-op runner (framework).\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m1"],"parent":"bn-1kr","size":"m","title":"Field1 scalar-field type + image.extract_channel@1 + image.assemble_channels@1"}	blake3:REyMr1U1Bx9F-ttrC_4JGVo0um1MD9lacJ89FK8kAfU
1781978495254284	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzSg		item.create	bn-p51	{"description":"**What:** Synthesize an `Image` in-graph from a descriptor + fill value (OP_CATALOG §1). Validates extent/range/\nformat; the fill respects the declared color/scalar semantics.\n**Acceptance:** created image has exact extent/range/format; out-of-range fill rejected per valid-range policy; deterministic.\n**Exit gate:** `cargo xtask verify-op image.create@1` passes (extent/range/format exactness, range rejection); `just check` → 0.\n**Refs:** OP_CATALOG §1; plan.md §8.3.\n**Depends on:** verify-op runner.\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m1"],"parent":"bn-1kr","size":"s","title":"Op: image.create@1 (descriptor + fill → Image)"}	blake3:d7nTQ6P9gOjFUZnTGniAOHqWE9HtK_-VPucjeTQZ8yg
1781978495358276	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzSw		item.create	bn-18q	{"description":"**What:** Primitive masks: `mask.empty` (all 0, exact), `mask.full` (all 1, exact), `mask.rect` (half-open pixel\nconvention, analytic antialiasing). Extent from descriptor or `extent_from` input.\n**Acceptance:** empty all-zero, full all-one (exact); rect coverage matches analytic area, half-open `[x0,x1)×[y0,y1)` exact on pixel-aligned cases (§3.6); tile boundary does not alter coverage.\n**Exit gate:** `cargo xtask verify-op mask.empty@1 / mask.full@1 / mask.rect@1` pass (exactness + half-open convention + area convergence); `just check` → 0.\n**Refs:** OP_CATALOG §3; AGENT_VERIFICATION §3.6; IR_SPEC §8.1.\n**Depends on:** verify-op runner.\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m1"],"parent":"bn-1kr","size":"s","title":"Op: mask.empty@1 + mask.full@1 + mask.rect@1"}	blake3:z3XCi3V2MuPUkT_UJwYIh1vOYpqdVCj6wnP3k8tGIdY
1781978495461897	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzTA		item.create	bn-2qz	{"description":"**What:** Rasterize a polygon mask with explicit fill rule (`nonzero` winding / `even-odd`) and analytic-ish\nantialiasing; handle degenerate/self-touching edges without NaN (OP_CATALOG §3).\n**Acceptance:** area converges to analytic polygon area with resolution; fill rule honored on a self-intersecting test polygon; degenerate edges produce finite coverage; 90° rotation/reflection covariance; half-open convention.\n**Exit gate:** `cargo xtask verify-op mask.polygon@1` passes (area convergence, fill-rule fixtures, degenerate-edge fixture, rotation metamorphic); `just check` → 0.\n**Refs:** OP_CATALOG §3; AGENT_VERIFICATION §3.6, §2.9 (degenerate polygons).\n**Depends on:** verify-op runner.\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m1"],"parent":"bn-1kr","size":"m","title":"Op: mask.polygon@1 (winding/even-odd, degenerate edges)"}	blake3:4bb8ZJhw2yoz_jSr_u_-5fCu0gSbEP89f_1HCxPTBbY
1781978495568171	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzTQ		item.create	bn-3sj	{"description":"**What:** `mask.invert`, `mask.union`, `mask.intersect`, `mask.subtract` with explicit hard vs soft (fuzzy)\nalgebra variants (OP_CATALOG §4). Soft variant operates on coverage in [0,1] with a declared fuzzy algebra.\n**Acceptance (hard masks, AGENT_VERIFICATION §2.5 mask algebra):** commutativity, associativity, idempotence (A∪A=A), complement laws, De Morgan, A−A=∅, double-inverse. For soft masks, only the laws the chosen fuzzy algebra defines.\n**Exit gate:** `cargo xtask verify-op mask.invert@1 / mask.union@1 / mask.intersect@1 / mask.subtract@1` pass (the algebra property suite for hard masks; declared-law subset for soft); `just check` → 0.\n**Refs:** OP_CATALOG §4; AGENT_VERIFICATION §2.5.\n**Depends on:** mask.empty + mask.full + mask.rect (primitives to test against); verify-op runner.\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m1"],"parent":"bn-1kr","size":"m","title":"Op: mask boolean algebra — invert/union/intersect/subtract@1 (hard + soft)"}	blake3:yKqmHx_hgVZ2W77kOk34eCMiAzxTFmmZS27dM2Jun5M
1781978495671565	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzTg		item.create	bn-2pz	{"description":"**What:** Report tight bounds + occupancy of a mask's nonzero region (OP_CATALOG §4). Defined empty-mask behavior.\n**Acceptance:** bounds match analytic geometry for rect/ellipse masks; empty mask → well-defined empty bounds (not a panic); occupancy counts correct.\n**Exit gate:** `cargo xtask verify-op mask.bounds@1` passes (analytic bounds, empty-mask behavior); `just check` → 0.\n**Refs:** OP_CATALOG §4.\n**Depends on:** mask.empty + mask.full + mask.rect; verify-op runner.\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m1"],"parent":"bn-1kr","size":"xs","title":"Op: mask.bounds@1 (Mask → Report)"}	blake3:2L4ggFsGtHUQ_E_o70jzJ3cUL37H-4cIZ_xDoFULHGs
1781978495777594	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzTw		item.create	bn-1nt	{"description":"**What:** `image.crop` (rect, half-open bounds, exact) and `image.pad` (margins + boundary mode; negative padding\nrejected or normalized to crop) (OP_CATALOG §5).\n**Acceptance:** crop is exact pixel selection on half-open bounds; pad fills per boundary mode (constant/clamp/mirror/wrap); crop∘pad round-trip identity on the interior; negative pad handled per policy.\n**Exit gate:** `cargo xtask verify-op image.crop@1 / image.pad@1` pass (exactness, boundary-mode fixtures, round-trip); `just check` → 0.\n**Refs:** OP_CATALOG §5; IR_SPEC §8.1, §8.4.\n**Depends on:** verify-op runner.\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m1"],"parent":"bn-1kr","size":"s","title":"Op: image.crop@1 + image.pad@1"}	blake3:tthzeHkvvWs6NBeWUOS2BYhz40nOlOKVq59VMqXN4y0
1781978495884648	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzUA		item.create	bn-2yy	{"description":"**What:** Resize with fixed-definition resamplers: nearest, bilinear, bicubic (fixed cubic parameter), Lanczos\n(fixed lobe count). Pixel-center convention and each kernel's support/halo are declared (OP_CATALOG §5).\n**Acceptance (AGENT_VERIFICATION §3.8):** identity scale → identity; integer translation with nearest → exact; constant-preserving for normalized kernels; output independent of tiling; each kernel declares support+halo; band-limited up/down round-trip within declared tolerance.\n**Exit gate:** `cargo xtask verify-op image.resize@1` passes (per-resampler property set + differential vs reference + tiling-independence); `just check` → 0.\n**Refs:** OP_CATALOG §5; AGENT_VERIFICATION §3.8.\n**Depends on:** verify-op runner.\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m1"],"parent":"bn-1kr","size":"l","title":"Op: image.resize@1 (nearest / bilinear / bicubic / Lanczos)"}	blake3:QzB868L43bgl5gGTEHbxjk4Aby6MDtwq_sBjvg9Mm0A
1781978495991464	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzUQ		item.create	bn-4k5	{"description":"**What:** Axis flip and quarter-turn rotation, exact integer remaps (OP_CATALOG §5). These are not only ops but\nthe machinery many metamorphic tests use (90° rotation covariance, reflection covariance — §2.5).\n**Acceptance:** double-flip identity; four rotate90 → identity; exact pixel correspondence (no resampling); extent transforms correctly.\n**Exit gate:** `cargo xtask verify-op image.flip@1 / image.rotate90@1` pass (involution/identity, exact correspondence); `just check` → 0.\n**Refs:** OP_CATALOG §5; AGENT_VERIFICATION §2.5.\n**Depends on:** verify-op runner.\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m1"],"parent":"bn-1kr","size":"xs","title":"Op: image.flip@1 + image.rotate90@1 (metamorphic-test infrastructure)"}	blake3:4I-KwZnnsG3mmySURYzx_ACkaK7WiefO4LWh2v3-Vvw
1781978496099634	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzUg		item.create	bn-20o	{"description":"**What:** Fill an image/field with a typed scalar/color value through an optional mask (OP_CATALOG §6).\n**Acceptance:** empty-mask identity; full-mask == constant; value respects color/scalar semantics; finite; no change outside mask at reference precision.\n**Exit gate:** `cargo xtask verify-op paint.fill@1` passes (masked identity properties, type correctness); `just check` → 0.\n**Refs:** OP_CATALOG §6.\n**Depends on:** verify-op runner.\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m1"],"parent":"bn-1kr","size":"s","title":"Op: paint.fill@1 (typed scalar/color fill, masked)"}	blake3:dMRX-lDYXztJAwx3KSL8Zqgq28bNsCr6-C8vGteTtOA
1781978496203102	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzUw		item.create	bn-2oo	{"description":"**What:** Linear and radial gradients with explicit stop interpolation and color space; degenerate radii handled\n(OP_CATALOG §6). Output image or field.\n**Acceptance:** stop values reproduced exactly at stop positions; interpolation matches the declared space; monotonic parameterization; degenerate (zero-radius) radial rejected or defined; translation/rotation covariance for linear gradient.\n**Exit gate:** `cargo xtask verify-op paint.linear_gradient@1 / paint.radial_gradient@1` pass (stop exactness, interpolation, degenerate handling, metamorphic); `just check` → 0.\n**Refs:** OP_CATALOG §6.\n**Depends on:** verify-op runner.\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m1"],"parent":"bn-1kr","size":"m","title":"Op: paint.linear_gradient@1 + paint.radial_gradient@1"}	blake3:oaGTsazL7qJ_A_VnllS512dko7CaxmaNiI201gAaXX4
1781978496310297	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzVA		item.create	bn-2ay	{"description":"**What:** Premultiplied linear `over`: `C_o = C_s + C_d(1−α_s)`, `α_o = α_s + α_d(1−α_s)` (OP_CATALOG §7;\nAGENT_VERIFICATION §3.2).\n**Acceptance:** transparent source identity; opaque source replacement; output α in [0,1]; premultiplied constraint |C_i|≤α; associativity within tolerance; no colored fringe on alpha-edge fixtures after export.\n**Exit gate:** `cargo xtask verify-op composite.over@1` passes (the §3.2 property set incl. fringe fixture); `just check` → 0.\n**Refs:** OP_CATALOG §7; AGENT_VERIFICATION §3.2.\n**Depends on:** verify-op runner.\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m1"],"parent":"bn-1kr","size":"s","title":"Op: composite.over@1 (premultiplied alpha-over)"}	blake3:NrPObD5zN3wok84g1PqJ1QPUYj7TeD4Sc38hRd-IJHA
1781978496417469	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzVQ		item.create	bn-1y2	{"description":"**What:** Blend with opacity + optional mask over the restricted, exactly-pinned mode set: normal/over, add,\nsubtract, multiply, screen, darken, lighten, difference (overlay/soft-light deferred until their exact semantics\nare pinned). Each mode has a documented formula + color space (OP_CATALOG §7).\n**Acceptance:** each mode matches its documented formula on analytic fixtures; opacity=0 identity; mask=0 identity; commutative modes verified commutative; finite.\n**Exit gate:** `cargo xtask verify-op composite.blend@1` passes (per-mode formula fixtures, identity properties); `just check` → 0.\n**Refs:** OP_CATALOG §7.\n**Depends on:** composite.over@1; verify-op runner.\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m1"],"parent":"bn-1kr","size":"m","title":"Op: composite.blend@1 (restricted modes)"}	blake3:xIERleUU9SH3neDR6sX39GMBWvxqSQYpKgp_qxpgbFs
1781978496523265	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzVg		item.create	bn-21l	{"description":"**What:** Direct convolution CPU reference — the semantic oracle for all later optimized/separable/FFT paths\n(OP_CATALOG §8; M1 deliverable). Supports all boundary modes (constant/clamp/mirror/wrap/transparent/valid-only),\narbitrary small kernels, on images and `Field1`.\n**Acceptance (AGENT_VERIFICATION §3.3):** impulse response == kernel (interior); constant scales by kernel sum; unit-sum preserves constants; zero-sum → 0 on constant interior; linearity before clamp; translation equivariance away from boundaries; boundary mode is part of the op hash and tested.\n**Exit gate:** `cargo xtask verify-op filter.convolve@1` passes (the §3.3 property set + per-boundary-mode fixtures + translation metamorphic); `just check` → 0.\n**Refs:** OP_CATALOG §8; AGENT_VERIFICATION §3.3; IR_SPEC §8.4.\n**Depends on:** Field1 type; verify-op runner.\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m1"],"parent":"bn-1kr","size":"l","title":"Op: filter.convolve@1 (direct CPU reference oracle, all boundary modes)"}	blake3:XuXm9i4ULIF2BoxtiKd8W7rXen_bkA_vlZ8QZaGY3dc
1781978496628380	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzVw		item.create	bn-1vt	{"description":"**What:** Gaussian blur reference semantics built on `filter.convolve` with a sampled/normalized Gaussian kernel\n(the separable/optimized path is M3). Declares halo = ceil(3σ) and sigma→0 cutoff policy (OP_CATALOG §8).\n**Acceptance (AGENT_VERIFICATION §3.4):** positive unit-sum kernel; constant-preserving; isotropic under 90° rotations; semigroup G_σ1*G_σ2 ≈ G_√(σ1²+σ2²) within discretization bound; blurred-impulse variance matches requested within bound; σ→0 → identity under cutoff policy.\n**Exit gate:** `cargo xtask verify-op filter.gaussian_blur@1` passes (the §3.4 properties + differential vs filter.convolve with the same kernel); `just check` → 0.\n**Refs:** OP_CATALOG §8; AGENT_VERIFICATION §3.4.\n**Depends on:** filter.convolve@1; verify-op runner.\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m1"],"parent":"bn-1kr","size":"m","title":"Op: filter.gaussian_blur@1 (CPU reference via direct convolution)"}	blake3:YZHTn4En7CK4v8E4Lp2mxirx-AoWdZHCtz-jsjQan64
1781978496731695	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzWA		item.create	bn-2fp	{"description":"**What:** `analyze.statistics` (resource + optional mask → report: count/min/max/mean/var, finite stats, stable\nreduction tree) and `analyze.histogram` (explicit bins + domain → histogram) (OP_CATALOG §12).\n**Acceptance:** stats exact on analytic fixtures (constant/ramp); reduction order is deterministic (stable merge tree — sets up M2 deterministic reductions); histogram bin assignment correct at bin edges; masked stats restrict correctly.\n**Exit gate:** `cargo xtask verify-op analyze.statistics@1 / analyze.histogram@1` pass (analytic exactness, determinism, bin-edge fixtures); `just check` → 0.\n**Refs:** OP_CATALOG §12; AGENT_VERIFICATION §2.4 (deterministic reductions).\n**Depends on:** verify-op runner.\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m1"],"parent":"bn-1kr","size":"s","title":"Op: analyze.statistics@1 + analyze.histogram@1"}	blake3:y7FL1B7bHOf4_Q2Xjp6B-ICRGm_AZWCugTq7Olr4Tzk
1781978496838689	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzWQ		item.create	bn-2mz	{"description":"**What:** `analyze.changed_bounds` (diff + threshold → bounds report; defined empty behavior) and the remaining P0\nassertions: `assert.range` (field/image within [min,max], count + worst value), `assert.alpha_valid` (range +\npremultiplied constraint), `assert.changed_bounds` (changed region contained in an expected box) — all typed nodes\nmapping failure to exit class 6 (OP_CATALOG §12; IR_SPEC §13).\n**Acceptance:** changed_bounds exact on known deltas + empty on identity; assert.range fails with worst-value + count on an out-of-range fixture; assert.alpha_valid fails on |C|>α; assert.changed_bounds fails when change escapes the box, with an artifact; `metric` severity never fails the run.\n**Exit gate:** `cargo xtask verify-op analyze.changed_bounds@1 / assert.range@1 / assert.alpha_valid@1 / assert.changed_bounds@1` pass (positive + failing cases with artifacts + severity behavior); `just check` → 0.\n**Refs:** OP_CATALOG §12; IR_SPEC §13; plan.md §15.4.\n**Depends on:** analyze.diff (MVP) [bn-1kx]; verify-op runner.\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m1"],"parent":"bn-1kr","size":"m","title":"Op: analyze.changed_bounds@1 + assert.range@1 + assert.alpha_valid@1 + assert.changed_bounds@1"}	blake3:SEAJSuLUJy8gNBXwtJdo7m3uleqpYCIg5roifxR9gDo
1781978496947434	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzWg		item.create	bn-2rx	{"description":"**What:** Close M1 (plan.md §19): confirm every op in the P0 set (OP_CATALOG §18) has a manifest and passes\n`verify-op`; expand the conformance suite so the full P0 set is exercised; and demonstrate the M1 acceptance\ncriterion — an agent completes a *new* fixture edit (different from the MVP blemish scenario, e.g. a masked\ngradient + blur + composite) using ONLY CLI introspection (`op list`/`op schema`) and the evidence bundle, with a\npassing no-change-outside-mask assertion.\n**Acceptance:** `paintop op list` shows the full P0 set, all with manifests; every P0 op's `verify-op` is green in CI; the new agent-authored conformance plan runs to exit 0 with a passing localization assertion and a reproducible rerun hash.\n**Exit gate:** CI \"P0 conformance\" job green (all verify-op + the two conformance scenarios + reproducibility reruns); `just check` → 0.\n**Refs:** plan.md §19 (M1 exit criteria); OP_CATALOG §18; AGENT_VERIFICATION §6.\n**Depends on:** ALL M1 op bones.\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m1"],"parent":"bn-1kr","size":"m","title":"M1 exit-criteria gate: full P0 conformance + agent-authored fixture edit"}	blake3:zI_2KES5RXZfvpQ354ENvs1U3kBKmum5KgtnY1ELoqY
