1781978580036183	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzhAE		item.create	bn-56s	{"description":"**What:** Implement the separable linear-time squared-Euclidean distance transform (Felzenszwalb–Huttenlocher,\ncs.brown.edu/people/pfelzens/papers/dt-final.pdf) as a `paintop-cpu` library primitive operating on a binary/\nthresholded set, plus an O(n²)-ish **brute-force EDT oracle** for differential testing on small images. This is the\nfoundation under all SDF ops — it is a primitive + oracle, not a public graph op yet.\n**Acceptance (AGENT_VERIFICATION §3.7 + ALIEN_OPS §2.5):** exact agreement with brute force on small fixtures; distance gradient magnitude ≈ 1 away from the medial axis; Euclidean rotation covariance on symmetric fixtures; correct on degenerate (all-empty / all-full / single-pixel) inputs.\n**Exit gate:** `cargo test -p paintop-cpu` EDT suite — separable-vs-brute differential (max abs error 0 on integer fixtures) + gradient-norm + rotation-covariance properties pass; `just check` → 0. (No verify-op: not a public op.)\n**Refs:** RESEARCH §3.1; ALIEN_OPS §2.4/§2.5; plan.md M4 (EDT); AGENT_VERIFICATION §3.7.\n**Depends on:** verify-op runner (framework); Field1 type [M1 bn-34g].\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m15"],"parent":"bn-9oi","size":"l","title":"Exact Euclidean distance transform (Felzenszwalb–Huttenlocher) + brute-force oracle"}	blake3:sLEBriYITNMJwbC-z_ZYoJeUaMo2A58NGpJFaXKsRCY
1781978580157444	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzhQE		item.create	bn-ez1	{"description":"**What:** Convert a hard/thresholded mask to a signed-distance field in physical pixel units (OP_CATALOG §4),\nusing the EDT primitive for inside and outside sets and combining signs. The sign convention\n(`negative-inside`) is explicit and never implicit (IR_SPEC §7.4). Soft-mask input requires an explicit contour\nthreshold or a declared generalized-distance policy — do NOT pretend a soft coverage map has one unique SDF.\n**Acceptance (AGENT_VERIFICATION §3.7):** sign correct inside/outside; zero contour corresponds to the declared threshold boundary; circle/rectangle analytic distances match away from rasterized-boundary ambiguity; brute-force differential on small images.\n**Exit gate:** `cargo xtask verify-op mask.to_sdf@1` passes (analytic circle/rect distances, sign correctness, brute-force differential); `just check` → 0.\n**Refs:** OP_CATALOG §4; IR_SPEC §7.4, §9.3; ALIEN_OPS §2.\n**Depends on:** Exact EDT primitive; verify-op runner.\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m15"],"parent":"bn-9oi","size":"m","title":"Op: mask.to_sdf@1 (Mask + contour policy → SdfMask)"}	blake3:e5qZiofGmWPUTdLYh6pYOFby4Dir_PmABzxiP1o5XeA
1781978580271754	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzhgE		item.create	bn-1jo	{"description":"**What:** `sdf.to_mask` (SdfMask + reconstruction profile, e.g. `smoothstep` with `half_width_px` → Mask, physical\nfeather width) and `sdf.offset` (grow/shrink by signed distance: φ' = φ − d) (OP_CATALOG §4; ALIEN_OPS §2.1).\n**Acceptance (AGENT_VERIFICATION §3.7):** offset composition `offset(offset(s,d1),d2) = offset(s,d1+d2)`; grow/shrink by zero is identity; reconstructed feather width matches `half_width_px` in physical pixels; sdf.to_mask of an un-offset SDF round-trips the original hard mask at the zero contour.\n**Exit gate:** `cargo xtask verify-op sdf.to_mask@1 / sdf.offset@1` pass (offset composition law, zero-identity, feather-width property, contour round-trip); `just check` → 0.\n**Refs:** OP_CATALOG §4; ALIEN_OPS §2.1; AGENT_VERIFICATION §3.7.\n**Depends on:** mask.to_sdf@1; verify-op runner.\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m15"],"parent":"bn-9oi","size":"m","title":"Op: sdf.to_mask@1 + sdf.offset@1"}	blake3:mkGPn3ujIWeKQEWnPRpRB9qI0A2XthAohjiXelFf08M
1781978580382997	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzhwE		item.create	bn-24u	{"description":"**What:** Boolean SDF algebra: union = `min(φ_A,φ_B)`, intersect = `max(φ_A,φ_B)`, subtract = `max(φ_A,−φ_B)`\n(OP_CATALOG §4; ALIEN_OPS §2.1). (smooth_union / sdf.normal / sdf.curvature are P2/R — deferred.)\n**Acceptance:** results agree with hard-mask boolean algebra when thresholded at the zero contour (cross-check against `mask.union/intersect/subtract`); commutativity for union/intersect; difference law for subtract; gradient-norm ≈ 1 preserved away from new medial axes.\n**Exit gate:** `cargo xtask verify-op sdf.union@1 / sdf.intersect@1 / sdf.subtract@1` pass (zero-contour agreement with hard-mask algebra + commutativity/difference laws); `just check` → 0.\n**Refs:** OP_CATALOG §4; ALIEN_OPS §2.1.\n**Depends on:** sdf.to_mask + sdf.offset; mask boolean algebra [M1 bn-3sj]; verify-op runner.\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m15"],"parent":"bn-9oi","size":"s","title":"Op: sdf.union@1 + sdf.intersect@1 + sdf.subtract@1"}	blake3:565ICZbyNfORscDPICJ0L406p06W2mNjm1LAEwaH_Cw
1781978580494131	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEziAE		item.create	bn-1ne	{"description":"**What:** Compatibility convenience macros (OP_CATALOG §4 note): `mask.grow`/`mask.shrink`/`mask.feather` that\n**normalize during canonicalization** into explicit `mask.to_sdf → sdf.offset → sdf.to_mask` subgraphs. The\nnormalized plan always exposes the expanded SDF nodes (plan.md §17 macro rule); the macro hides nothing semantic.\n**Acceptance:** a plan using `mask.feather` canonicalizes to the explicit SDF subgraph and produces an identical semantic hash to the hand-written expansion; macro params map deterministically to SDF params; round-trip through normalize is stable.\n**Exit gate:** test: macro plan and its hand-expanded SDF equivalent have identical semantic hashes and identical output; `just check` → 0.\n**Refs:** OP_CATALOG §4 note; plan.md §4.2, §17 (macros); IR_SPEC §17.\n**Depends on:** sdf.to_mask + sdf.offset; Canonicalization module [M0 bn-1e0]; verify-op runner.\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m15"],"parent":"bn-9oi","size":"s","title":"Macros: mask.grow / mask.shrink / mask.feather (normalize to SDF nodes)"}	blake3:C6fVMKiBCKEeEJ79hk5ZlnFzcoDomIg_o7k5Wa-F1Ig
1781978580609821	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEziQE		item.create	bn-iow	{"description":"**What:** Add the `LabelMap` (u32 IDs) resource type and three topology ops on hard masks (OP_CATALOG §4):\n`mask.connected_components` (→ LabelMap + report, explicit connectivity + label-stability policy),\n`mask.fill_holes` (border-connected definition), `mask.remove_components` (by area/connectivity policy).\n**Acceptance:** connected components count + labels correct on synthetic multi-blob fixtures with a deterministic label-stability policy; fill_holes fills only non-border-connected background; remove_components drops exactly the below-threshold blobs; 4- vs 8-connectivity honored; LabelMap round-trips without ID loss (large-ID fixture).\n**Exit gate:** `cargo xtask verify-op mask.connected_components@1 / mask.fill_holes@1 / mask.remove_components@1` pass (synthetic-blob fixtures, connectivity, label stability, large-ID integrity); `just check` → 0.\n**Refs:** OP_CATALOG §4; AGENT_VERIFICATION §2.3 (large-ID label map).\n**Depends on:** mask primitives [M1 bn-18q]; verify-op runner.\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m15"],"parent":"bn-9oi","size":"m","title":"Op: mask topology — connected_components@1 + fill_holes@1 + remove_components@1 (+ LabelMap)"}	blake3:GhU49tzW8wDbbhgY1XazXto5T5DIMV1jVBSMIK1K6EY
1781978580727640	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzigE		item.create	bn-18h	{"description":"**What:** Close M1.5: check in the **original SDF north-star variant** as a conformance scenario — the\n`mask.ellipse → mask.to_sdf → sdf.offset → sdf.to_mask` feather chain feeding the same touch-up loop — and prove it\nruns end-to-end with a passing localization assertion and a reproducible rerun hash. This is the scenario the M0\ndecision deferred (M0_DECISIONS.md D1); landing it here vindicates \"SDF lands second.\"\n**Acceptance:** `paintop run conformance/plans/blemish-sdf.json --bundle run/` → exit 0 with passing no-change-outside-mask; rerun produces a byte-identical hash; EDT brute-force differential, offset-composition, and boolean SDF laws all green in CI.\n**Exit gate:** CI \"M1.5 SDF conformance\" job green (SDF scenario + reproducibility + the SDF property suites); `just check` → 0.\n**Refs:** M0_DECISIONS.md D1; OP_CATALOG §4; plan.md §25 (original SDF variant); ALIEN_OPS §2.\n**Depends on:** ALL M1.5 op bones.\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m15"],"parent":"bn-9oi","size":"s","title":"M1.5 exit gate: SDF north-star variant end-to-end"}	blake3:n94ZuvSJkPInlBeJft1TuPbKdSl1vIRKZk7hIHhqKus
