1781979709437464	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzywI		item.comment	bn-we1	{"body":"Created during grooming because plan.md §19 lists fuzz scaffolding in M0, but existing quality bones only covered fmt/clippy/test/doc, verify-op, fixtures, and conformance. This keeps fuzzing as a bounded smoke/nightly quality gate rather than slowing every local just check."}	blake3:IIii7R0broqj5smgaRMorCHlw0itFqKAIZNhvOc9d68
1781979744972106	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzzAI		item.update	bn-we1	{"field":"description","value":"Add the initial fuzz harness expected by plan.md §19 M0 and AGENT_VERIFICATION quality goals.\n\nScope:\n- Introduce a standard Rust fuzz setup (`cargo-fuzz`/libFuzzer or the repo-approved equivalent) without making it part of every local `just check`.\n- Add seed corpus directories and two first targets:\n  1. Strict plan parsing/canonicalization rejects malformed JSON, duplicate-key-like structures, invalid numbers, excessive nesting/size, and unknown fields without panics or unbounded allocation.\n  2. PNG decode/encode boundary fuzzing exercises malformed, truncated, and oversized inputs through the hardened decode limits without panics.\n\nAcceptance criteria:\n- Fuzz targets build in CI/nightly or an explicit `just fuzz-smoke` job.\n- The smoke job runs for a bounded time suitable for CI.\n- Crash artifacts are captured under `target/fuzz/artifacts` with reproduction instructions.\n\nReferences: plan.md §17.2, §19 M0; AGENT_VERIFICATION §2.1/§2.2."}	blake3:Ibk7FVj-eMfe1FWGF8MgergobNKSYF-i-MCuQ__T6Uw
1781979757694522	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzzQI		item.update	bn-3bj	{"field":"description","value":"**What:** Wire the plan.md §19 M0 exit criteria into CI as a gate, confirm the M1 \"all operations have manifests\" criterion holds for the MVP ops, and include the bounded fuzz-smoke coverage required by M0. Write a short `docs/` + README \"how to run the loop\" plus the agent completion-report template (AGENT_VERIFICATION §6.1). Final tidy: ensure all MVP ops register manifests and pass verify-op.\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- CI M0 gate is green and runs: `cargo fmt --check`; `cargo clippy --workspace --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings` (pedantic+nursery+unwrap denies); `cargo test --workspace`; `cargo doc --workspace --no-deps`; `paintop validate fixtures/plans/empty-valid.json` (0); `paintop validate fixtures/plans/unknown-field.json` (fails predictably).\n- Fuzz smoke coverage from `bn-we1` is wired into CI/nightly or an explicit bounded `just fuzz-smoke` job and records reproduction instructions for any crash artifact.\n- Every MVP op has a manifest; `op list` shows all 14; each passes `verify-op`.\n- A fresh-clone walkthrough (`just check` → run the conformance loop) is documented and verified.\n- The M0 + first-half-M1 exit-criteria checklist is ticked with evidence paths.\n\n**Exit gate (must pass to close):** the CI M0 gate passes on a clean checkout; the fuzz smoke job builds and runs within its bound; the documented fresh-clone walkthrough works end-to-end; `just check` → 0.\n**Testing strategy:** CI gate + bounded fuzz smoke + a documented manual fresh-clone smoke.\n**References:** plan.md §19 (M0 + M1 exit criteria); AGENT_VERIFICATION §2.1, §2.2, §6.1.\n**Depends on:** paintop CLI; verify-op runner; End-to-end conformance; fuzz scaffolding."}	blake3:Z0rNf-Wb1M9IcBfvEdH8gNKwL-t0sxxBF64OGXk9v0U
1781979765611350	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzzgI		item.comment	bn-1yc	{"body":"Grooming results: existing bones already cover the D2 14-op MVP loop, M1/P0 conformance set from OP_CATALOG §18, M1.5 SDF split, M2 gates, verify-op, analytic fixtures, evidence, and milestone dependency ordering. Added bn-we1 for missing M0 fuzz scaffolding and wired it into bn-3bj. Added bn-347 for D1 doc alignment, verified docs already satisfy it, and closed it with evidence. Updated bn-3bj to include fuzz smoke in the M0 gate."}	blake3:GYXHRPrtUvtWOYor1CBTJrkC09N6SFvo6Man3hvzHqM
1781979765627663	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzzwI		item.move	bn-1yc	{"state":"done"}	blake3:ru5L17RYsH2wsmc891stBONiZ6VvLjK2E2TBNRJDBSE
1781979981646481	bob	itc:v3:AWKSc8kyZJPJk5EAAAAAQau9WtV610AAAAEzAQ		item.update	bn-31z	{"field":"title","value":"Operation manifest model, registry, OpContract trait, and schema export"}	blake3:HyJTRXtrMLCTZQGZlYEuKeeIc4GUBTmRMDAupypz_Tc
1781979981663858	bob	itc:v3:AWKSc8kyZJPJk5EAAAAAQau9WtV610AAAAEzAg		item.update	bn-31z	{"field":"description","value":"**What:** `OpManifest` types (plan.md §9): stable id + semantic major, input/output ports & resource types,\nparameter schema + defaults, semantics block (purity, color_requirement, alpha_requirement, roi, halo,\ndeterminism tier, seed requirement), available implementations, mathematical properties, limits, reference\nfixture ids. A registry keyed by `namespace.name@major` that rejects duplicate ids and dangling implementation\nrefs. The `OpContract` trait (IR_SPEC §18: `infer_outputs`, `required_inputs`, `validate_postconditions`).\nA manifest↔Rust-impl agreement check (ports and defaults must match). Generate `schemas/op-manifest-v1.schema.json`.\n\n**Why:** Manifests drive validation, scheduling, testing, and agent introspection (`op list`/`op schema`). Every\nop bone registers one.\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- A sample manifest loads and validates against the generated JSON Schema.\n- Registry rejects duplicate op ids and unknown implementation references with typed errors.\n- `OpContract` is object-safe and implemented by a stub op; a test asserts manifest ports == stub impl ports/defaults.\n- `infer_outputs`/`required_inputs`/`validate_postconditions` are deterministic and cheap (documented contract, IR_SPEC §18).\n\n**Exit gate (must pass to close):** `cargo test` manifest/registry/contract suite passes; `schemas/op-manifest-v1.schema.json` is generated and checked in; `just check` → 0.\n**Testing strategy:** Unit tests for registry invariants + a manifest/impl agreement test for a stub op.\n**References:** plan.md §9, §24; IR_SPEC §18; OP_CATALOG §19.\n**Depends on:** Resource metadata enums; Error taxonomy"}	blake3:5ghmDoE-iZ_tcLx8y0RGWM6tSty4oRXcIexYz__YBR8
