1781990085501128	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzqgM		item.create	bn-28i	{"description":"**What:** The central `paintop-ir` `Error` is ~176 bytes, exceeding clippy's `result_large_err` 128-byte\nthreshold, so ~30 `#[allow(clippy::result_large_err, reason=...)]` hatches are now scattered across paintop-ir\nand paintop-testkit. Fix at the root: box the heavy payload inside `Error` (e.g. `Box<ErrorContext>` / boxed\ndetails) so `Error` is <=128 bytes and `Result<T, Error>` stays cheap, then DELETE every\n`result_large_err` allow across the workspace. Do NOT silence via `large-error-threshold` in clippy.toml —\nthe lint's intent (small Results) should actually hold.\n**Why:** Without this, every one of the remaining ~35 M0 bones keeps pasting the same allow. Fix once.\n**Acceptance:** `std::mem::size_of::<paintop_ir::Error>() <= 128` (assert in a test); zero occurrences of\n`result_large_err` in the tree (`grep -rn result_large_err crates xtask` empty); the error wire JSON\n(IR_SPEC §19 envelope) is byte-identical to before (golden test still passes); all existing tests pass.\n**Exit gate:** `just check` → 0 with NO result_large_err allows anywhere; size_of assertion test green.\n**Refs:** M0_DECISIONS.md D4 (structured error is the agent-facing contract); IR_SPEC §19.\n**Depends on:** error taxonomy [bn-2i9] (done).\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-ir"],"parent":"bn-6pu","size":"s","title":"Shrink central Error so Result is cheap; remove all result_large_err allows"}	blake3:U1J--8fHc1H66FKhdx2Z-iAq1DqTWAPfl-j3C1vN_VA
1781990085620238	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzqwM		item.create	bn-2l1	{"description":"**What:** Add a `normalize` step (IR_SPEC §17 rules) that produces the canonical semantic form a plan's\nsemantic hash is computed over. For M0 implement the rules that do NOT require op manifests: strip\nnon-semantic annotation fields (notably `description`, and any other documented non-semantic metadata),\napply structural canonicalization (key sort happens in the canonical emitter; ensure seeds/refs are in\nnormalized form), and route `hash_value`/plan semantic hashing THROUGH this normalizer. Manifest-driven\ndefault injection (§17 r2) is explicitly DEFERRED to when real op manifests exist (segment 2) — leave a\nclearly-named hook/TODO and a unit test marked for that follow-up; do not fake it.\n**Why:** Today two plans differing ONLY in `description` hash differently, violating §17 r1 (description is\nnon-semantic). This is the canonicalization goal's core guarantee and gates bn-1e0.\n**Acceptance:** two plans identical except for `description` (and whitespace/key-order) produce an\nIDENTICAL `blake3:` semantic hash; a plan differing in any real semantic field still hashes differently;\nthe normalizer is idempotent (normalize(normalize(x)) == normalize(x)); negative/round-trip fixtures pass.\n**Exit gate:** `just check` → 0; \"description-insensitive, semantics-sensitive hash\" test green; the\nmanifest-default-injection follow-up is captured as a tracked `#[ignore]`/TODO test, not silently omitted.\n**Refs:** IR_SPEC §17 (normalization rules); M0_DECISIONS.md D4; builds on bn-2yp/bn-1m3/bn-2ui.\n**Depends on:** canonical emitter [bn-2yp], semantic hash [bn-1m3], replay tests [bn-2ui] (all done).\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-ir"],"parent":"bn-1e0","size":"s","title":"Plan normalization (IR_SPEC §17): strip non-semantic fields before hashing"}	blake3:-V_PKR29q_gGPnoDMGlKD-h_179R7zt-b1V7XYboIg4
