1782010102346639	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEz0AQ		item.create	bn-2nr	{"description":"**What:** The CPU reference splat op (`crates/paintop-cpu/src/splat.rs`) currently evaluates **every splat\nat every pixel** — cost is O(width · height · n_splats) with a transcendental `exp` per (pixel, splat),\nsingle-threaded. Add per-splat **bounding-box / support culling**: for each splat, compute the axis-aligned\nbounding box of the rotated Gaussian's effective support (the region where the splat's contribution is\nnon-negligible — e.g. within `k`·σ along each principal axis, accounting for `angle_rad`) and only evaluate\npixels inside that box. A 1024×768 canvas with 6.5k small splats drops from ~5e9 `exp` calls to the sum of\nthe splats' covered areas (orders of magnitude fewer).\n**Why:** A full-resolution render of a dense scene can take minutes today, which reads as a hang and tempts\ncallers (human or agent) to kill the process. This is the single biggest constant-factor win available and\nneeds no parallelism or unsafe code.\n**Crucial constraint — must not change the output.** The cull must be *conservative*: pick the cutoff `k`\n(and handle the rotation/anisotropy correctly) so that every pixel skipped would have contributed a weight\nthat, after `opacity` scaling and f32 rounding into the accumulator, is provably below the representable\nthreshold — i.e. the rendered image is **bit-identical** to the un-culled reference for the op's existing\nfixtures. Do NOT trade correctness for speed; if a true bit-identical cutoff is impossible, keep the result\nwithin the op's declared `bounded` tolerance and document the bound explicitly. Array-order accumulation and\nall existing semantics (blend modes, premultiplied linear space, zero-opacity identity) are preserved.\n**Acceptance:**\n- A differential test renders a representative multi-splat batch with culling ON vs OFF and asserts the\n  outputs are **bit-identical** (or, if a documented tolerance is used, within it and the bound is asserted).\n- All existing `paint.gaussian_splats@1` verify-op categories still PASS unchanged (`cargo xtask verify-op\n  paint.gaussian_splats@1`).\n- A timing/area sanity check shows work scales with covered area, not W·H·n (e.g. a dense small-sigma batch on\n  a large canvas is dramatically faster; record before/after in the bone comments).\n- Degenerate inputs handled: a splat whose support covers the whole image falls back to full evaluation; a\n  splat entirely outside the canvas contributes nothing; huge/zero/near-zero sigma and rotated anisotropy are\n  all correct.\n**Exit gate:** `cargo xtask verify-op paint.gaussian_splats@1` PASS + the culling-vs-full bit-identical\ndifferential test green + `just check` → 0.\n**Testing strategy:** reuse the existing splat property/oracle fixtures as the differential baseline; add the\nwhole-image-support fallback case and an off-canvas case; keep the un-culled path available (e.g. behind a\ntest-only switch or as the differential reference) so the equivalence test is meaningful.\n**References:** crates/paintop-cpu/src/splat.rs; OP_CATALOG (paint.gaussian_splats); AGENT_VERIFICATION §3.x\n(splat properties); plan.md M3 (optimized CPU). Surfaced by a low-context agent that rendered a 6.5k-splat\n1024×768 castle and had to fall back to release + half-res previews because the full render took ~3 min.\n**Note:** Pure constant-factor optimization that preserves reference semantics; could be pulled ahead of the\nrest of M3 if splat-heavy rendering becomes a bottleneck sooner.\n**Depends on:** paint.gaussian_splats@1 [bn-1oa] (done).\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m3"],"parent":"bn-2ca","size":"m","title":"paint.gaussian_splats: bounding-box / support culling (O(pixels·splats) → O(covered area))"}	blake3:qgrjfq_RsR5ezzzeBPOZfElbkEl133dWOBnpM9ehYRA
