1782011358175198	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEz1AQ		item.create	bn-2ai	{"description":"Replace the single central manifests()/implementation_registry() vecs in crates/paintop-cpu/src/registry.rs with per-domain register(reg, impls) functions (io/color/paint/filter/mask/composite/analyze/assert/image). Central registry.rs iterates domains in explicit order — it changes ONLY when a whole new domain is added, so op-adding bones edit only their domain module and never conflict on a shared file. This unblocks parallel maw workspaces for M1.5/M2 op work.\n\nAcceptance:\n- Each op domain module exposes pub(crate) fn register(&mut OperationRegistry, &mut ImplRegistry) -> Result<(), Error>; registry.rs only lists domains.\n- Determinism preserved: explicit domain order then within-domain order (NO hashing/sort-by-id needed); operation_registry()/implementation_registry() produce byte-identical ordering to before.\n- Replace the brittle len()==N count test with a COMPLETENESS test: every ops/manifests/*.json has a registered impl AND every registered op has a manifest (catches a domain register fn that was never wired in).\n- No new dependencies (do NOT use inventory/linkme — link-time registration risks determinism + dead-code-elimination drops, M0_DECISIONS D4).\n- just check 0; all existing verify-op still pass unchanged; existing tests green.\n\nFront-load note: cross-cutting resource-type variant additions (Field1 already in M1; SdfMask, LabelMap for M1.5) remain serialization points — add those enum variants + domain register stubs in a small types-first batch BEFORE fanning out parallel op agents.\n\nRefs: registry.rs single-seam contention; plan.md §6.1 (cpu reference ownership); M0_DECISIONS D4 (deps/determinism).","kind":"task","title":"Refactor: partition op registry by domain (enable parallel op bones)"}	blake3:uJyJfpzBw5ciNYgRoV-k-P8mLqByv7QiblaVbZFwlGo
