1782028028568566	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEz5QU		item.create	bn-3ai	{"description":"Latent correctness gap flagged during M2 (bn-y0h). crates/paintop-core/src/tile/execute.rs execute_tiled()'s tileable() predicate tiles ANY RoiCategory::Pointwise op with >=1 input. This is sound ONLY for position-INDEPENDENT pointwise ops (output(x,y)=f(input(x,y))). paint.linear_gradient@1 / paint.radial_gradient@1 declare RoiCategory::Pointwise but are position-DEPENDENT (they read absolute pixel-center coordinates and ignore input samples except for extent). If such an op were tiled, cropping shifts the tile origin and it would produce WRONG results — silent, not a panic.\n\nCurrently NOT a live bug: execute_tiled is not yet wired into the production pipeline, and the differential tests deliberately use color.adjust (position-independent). But it MUST be fixed before tiled execution is wired into the real run path.\n\nFix options (pick one):\n- Add an explicit position-independence signal: a manifest flag (e.g. position_independent: bool) or a narrower ROI sub-category (Pointwise{PositionIndependent} vs Generator), and have tileable() require it.\n- OR have execute_tiled exclude generator-style ops (no semantic input dependence) from the tiled path and run them whole-image.\nAdd a differential test that tiling a gradient op equals whole-image (guarding against regression).\n\nRefs: M2 bn-y0h report; tile/execute.rs tileable(); plan.md §11. Parent: bn-2ca (M3 optimized backends) — this is a prerequisite for wiring tiles into the pipeline.","kind":"task","labels":["tracking"],"title":"Tile executor: guard position-dependent pointwise ops (gradients) before pipeline wiring"}	blake3:mtxmrINnGcap4Ynu1_1W-pTn8lZsApOgiDzcDB6ntZk
1782050858419017	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEz5gU		item.create	bn-3rx	{"description":"paint.gaussian_splats@1 currently supports only BlendMode Normal and Multiply (crates/paintop-cpu/src/splat.rs, enum BlendMode). Authoring an ocean-sunset test, an agent wanted additive 'add'/'screen' blending for sun-glitter glints and atmospheric glow and got a clean dispatch rejection — forcing Normal, which can't accumulate light. This is the single most-requested expressiveness gap for painterly splat work.\n\nAdd the additive/lightening modes to the splat BlendMode enum + token parser: at minimum screen and add (lighten/darken/difference optional for parity). The math ALREADY EXISTS and is verified in composite.blend@1 (crates/paintop-cpu/src/blend.rs: add=s+d, screen=s+d-s*d, lighten=max, darken=min, difference=|s-d|) operating on premultiplied-linear samples — reuse that exact per-channel formulation so splat blending stays consistent with composite.blend and remains DeterminismTier::Exact (closed-form, bit-identical).\n\nAcceptance:\n- New tokens parse (e.g. 'screen','add','lighten'); unknown tokens still rejected; default stays 'normal'.\n- Per-splat blend matches composite.blend's same-mode formula on premultiplied-linear samples (cross-check test).\n- screen/add are order-sensitivity-correct vs splat draw order; bit-identical reruns; verify-op paint.gaussian_splats@1 still passes (extend its fixtures to cover a screen/add splat).\n- just check 0.\n\nRefs: splat.rs BlendMode (Normal/Multiply only); blend.rs mode formulas; surfaced in /tmp/paintop_art3 sunset test. NOTE: anisotropic sigma_x/sigma_y + angle_rad already supported (no bone needed). Related perf lever already filed: bn-2nr (splat bbox culling) which would lift the density cap. A polyline brush (paint.stroke_splats) is already planned P1/M4.","kind":"task","title":"paint.gaussian_splats: additive blend modes (screen/add/lighten) for glints & glow"}	blake3:nGwTpgFYDRhxyNNjAyr5fWQeRuD3aiO7rYKqa6_DM0Q
1782052676529070	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEz5wU		item.create	bn-3rw	{"description":"paint.gaussian_splats@1 uses a pure-Gaussian spatial weight (crates/paintop-cpu/src/splat.rs: w(p) = opacity * exp(-0.5 * mahalanobis)). There is no way to get a crisper-edged or harder-core dab — every splat is the same soft Gaussian bell, which reads as foggy/blurry in dense painterly work. Add an optional per-splat 'hardness' (or 'profile') param controlling the falloff shape: e.g. a hardness in [0,1] that interpolates from the current Gaussian toward a hard-edged disk (a smoothstep core+edge, or remapping the normalized radius before the exp / a configurable falloff exponent). Default preserves today's exact Gaussian (hardness default = current behavior) so existing plans are unchanged.\n\nAcceptance:\n- Optional 'hardness' param (default = pure Gaussian, bit-identical to today); out-of-range/non-finite rejected.\n- Increasing hardness measurably sharpens the falloff (tested: coverage profile steeper; core flatter, edge tighter) while staying within the splat's support extent.\n- Closed-form + deterministic (DeterminismTier::Exact, bit-identical reruns).\n- verify-op paint.gaussian_splats@1 still passes (add a hardness fixture); just check 0.\n\nRefs: splat.rs weight() Gaussian-only; surfaced alongside the splat blend-modes gap in the sunset painterly-quality discussion. Companion to the splat additive-blend-modes bone + bn-2nr (culling/density).","kind":"task","title":"paint.gaussian_splats: per-splat falloff/hardness profile (crisper dabs)"}	blake3:mMfuFMfeqHSH37m0qrS7GpzUZgiTUWbdcTQBT8Iml24
1782052836471570	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEz6AU		item.create	bn-2b3	{"description":"**What:** The dispatch substrate every M3 optimization rides on (plan.md §6.1, §12). Generalize the executor so an op can carry MORE THAN ONE implementation (the manifest already names `cpu.reference`; add `cpu.optimized` / `wgpu.*` implementation ids per plan.md §20's `wgpu.separable@1` example) and the SCHEDULER selects a backend per op/subgraph from policy — ops request an execution strategy, they do NOT spawn their own parallelism (§12.2). Record the chosen backend + adapter/device identity in the evidence bundle (§12.3, §15). A backend that can't run an op cleanly falls back to the reference or emits an explicit unsupported error (never a silent wrong answer).\n**Acceptance:** an op with both a reference and an optimized impl runs either under scheduler/policy control, producing the SAME logical result (reference is the oracle); the evidence bundle records backend id per node; selecting a non-existent backend is an explicit typed error; default policy = reference (so existing plans are byte-identical).\n**Exit gate:** `cargo test` backend-dispatch suite (policy selection, evidence records backend, fallback/unsupported error) + `just check` 0.\n**Refs:** plan.md §6.1, §12.2/§12.3, §15; IR_SPEC (implementation id). **Depends on:** M2 executor/tile scheduler [bn-vim], evidence bundle [M0].\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m3"],"parent":"bn-2ca","size":"m","title":"Backend selection + dispatch (cpu.reference / cpu.optimized / wgpu)"}	blake3:TTodwlDuZubqNr_7S_DUo-3blJpwT6kTufKbT3EaH9I
1782052836598649	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEz6QU		item.create	bn-2oj	{"description":"**What:** The harness that validates EVERY non-reference backend against the CPU oracle (plan.md §11/§12, AGENT_VERIFICATION §3.x). Given an op + fixtures, run it on each available backend and assert the result is within the op's DECLARED tolerance contract (exact for exact-tier, bounded L2/Linf for bounded-tier), saving an error map on failure. Drives both the optimized-CPU and wgpu work; GPU cases skip cleanly when no adapter is present.\n**Acceptance:** running a known op on reference vs optimized backend passes within tolerance; an intentionally-wrong optimized kernel FAILS with an error map; GPU-absent → skipped, not failed; tolerance is read from the op's manifest/contract, not hard-coded per test.\n**Exit gate:** `cargo test`/`cargo xtask` cross-backend harness green on the existing optimized paths; `just check` 0.\n**Refs:** plan.md §11, §12; AGENT_VERIFICATION §3, §12. **Depends on:** Backend selection + dispatch.\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m3"],"parent":"bn-2ca","size":"m","title":"Cross-backend differential harness (optimized/GPU vs cpu.reference within tolerance)"}	blake3:0PJ1WX5mTmw87Ztr0NC9pqOl62u92NOVSQiBFTzd1lM
1782052836718428	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEz6gU		item.create	bn-3ny	{"description":"**What:** Parallelize the M2 tile executor across tiles with Rayon (plan.md §12.2), thread caps from policy, scheduler-owned (no nested uncontrolled parallelism, §12.2). Reductions stay deterministic via the M2 fixed merge trees so results are bit-identical regardless of thread count.\n**Acceptance:** a tiled pointwise + reduction chain produces BIT-IDENTICAL output across thread counts {1,2,8} and equal to the M2 single-threaded tiled result; thread cap from policy is honored; no op spawns its own pool.\n**Exit gate:** `cargo test` parallel-determinism suite (bit-identical across thread counts) + a throughput smoke; `just check` 0.\n**Refs:** plan.md §12.2; M2 deterministic reductions [bn-25j], tile executor [bn-y0h]. **Depends on:** Backend selection + dispatch; M2 tile executor.\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m3"],"parent":"bn-2ca","size":"m","title":"Rayon tile parallelism (deterministic, scheduler-owned)"}	blake3:QW3AI6RqXj2C2gGogGx7qnDSOV0QRBmXr8EaQPK4ECA
1782052836838568	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEz6wU		item.create	bn-nj3	{"description":"**What:** Explicit SIMD vectorized pointwise kernels for the hot pointwise ops (color.convert, color.adjust, alpha.premultiply/unpremultiply, composite.over/blend) as a `cpu.optimized` backend (plan.md §12.2). Precomputed kernels/LUTs carry a versioned precision tag. SIMD is added only where it beats scalar (benchmark-justified, §12.2).\n**Acceptance:** each SIMD kernel matches the scalar reference within the op's declared tolerance via the cross-backend harness (exact where the op is exact-tier); a benchmark shows real speedup vs scalar; no `unsafe` (use portable SIMD / autovectorization-friendly code under the lint wall) or, if intrinsics are unavoidable, isolate them behind a reviewed boundary consistent with D4 `unsafe_code = forbid`.\n**Exit gate:** cross-backend differential (SIMD vs reference) green for each kernel + a benchmark artifact; `just check` 0.\n**Refs:** plan.md §12.2; M0_DECISIONS D4 (unsafe forbid). **Depends on:** Cross-backend harness; Backend dispatch.\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m3"],"parent":"bn-2ca","size":"l","title":"SIMD pointwise kernels (vectorized cpu.optimized path)"}	blake3:kdkhDXQtSOEEZM8X2AufcCnj2Rx5itekuA3osPyRZps
1782052836958106	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEz7AU		item.create	bn-u6g	{"description":"**What:** A fast separable (two-pass) and/or recursive-IIR Gaussian blur as a `cpu.optimized` impl of filter.gaussian_blur@1, replacing the O(r) direct convolution for large sigma (plan.md §12.2 cache-aware separable passes). filter.gaussian_blur was declared DeterminismTier::Bounded in M1 specifically to allow this.\n**Acceptance:** optimized Gaussian matches the M1 direct-convolution reference within the declared bounded tolerance (cross-backend harness) across sigmas + boundary modes; meaningfully faster for large sigma (benchmark); deterministic/bit-identical reruns on a fixed backend.\n**Exit gate:** cross-backend differential (optimized vs reference) + benchmark; `just check` 0.\n**Refs:** plan.md §12.2; M1 gaussian_blur [bn-1vt]. **Depends on:** Cross-backend harness; Backend dispatch.\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m3"],"parent":"bn-2ca","size":"m","title":"Optimized separable / recursive Gaussian (cpu.optimized)"}	blake3:I5tz6_MjDzd9Wuh9VwVCEvASwRgvJBBFuSDNJnlGCDI
1782052837088876	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEz7QU		item.create	bn-7k0	{"description":"**What:** A benchmark harness that measures the optimized CPU (and later GPU) paths against the reference and emits performance baselines checked into CI artifacts (plan.md §19 M3 exit criterion 3). Stable, machine-tolerant methodology (report numbers + thresholds, do not hard-fail on absolute wall-clock on arbitrary CI hardware).\n**Acceptance:** `cargo bench`/xtask emits a baseline artifact (op, backend, size, throughput) uploaded by CI; a regression beyond a configurable threshold is flagged; baselines are reproducible enough to compare across runs.\n**Exit gate:** CI perf job produces + uploads the baseline artifact; `just check` 0.\n**Refs:** plan.md §19 (M3). **Depends on:** Rayon parallelism; SIMD kernels (something optimized to measure).\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m3"],"parent":"bn-2ca","size":"m","title":"Performance baselines + CI perf artifacts"}	blake3:sIHwAB1mvoZsZvOMz4t_8LfD9XNpal1m2Y9B6bS2ySU
1782052837209985	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEz7gU		item.create	bn-3u4	{"description":"**What:** Stand up the `paintop-wgpu` crate (plan.md §6, §12.3) PINNED at wgpu 27 to stay aligned with msh — NO wgpu major upgrade in this work (plan.md §12.3 / §19 constraint). Adapter/device acquisition, capability probe, pipeline cache keyed by normalized fused expression + format, storage-texture/buffer resource model, dispatch-dimension + overflow validation, adapter/device identity surfaced in the evidence bundle, and a CLEAN fallback (reference) or explicit unsupported error when no compatible GPU is present (§19 M3 exit criterion 4).\n**Acceptance:** on a machine with a GPU, device/adapter init succeeds and adapter identity appears in evidence; on a machine WITHOUT one, the runtime falls back cleanly or emits an explicit unsupported error (tested via a forced-no-adapter path) — never a crash or wrong result; pipeline cache returns the same pipeline for an identical fused key.\n**Exit gate:** `cargo test -p paintop-wgpu` (init, capability probe, forced-fallback, pipeline-cache key) — GPU-requiring tests gate on adapter presence; `just check` 0; wgpu stays at 27.\n**Refs:** plan.md §6, §12.3, §19 (M3); M0_DECISIONS (wgpu 27 / msh alignment). **Depends on:** Backend selection + dispatch.\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m3"],"parent":"bn-2ca","size":"l","title":"wgpu backend scaffolding: paintop-wgpu crate, device/adapter, fallback, evidence"}	blake3:gKJVTyELqbrZlfoXtHPXjCDuxJdaFhE8Lq7geespkNY
1782052837331568	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEz7wU		item.create	bn-1bg	{"description":"**What:** Fuse large pointwise chains into a single wgpu pipeline (plan.md §12.3, §10.1): group GPU-resident subgraphs to avoid intermediate readbacks, compile/cache the fused pipeline by normalized fused expression + format. The CPU oracle stays available for sampled differential checks.\n**Acceptance:** a multi-op pointwise chain runs entirely on GPU with NO intermediate host readback (trace-verified, plan.md §19 M3 exit criterion 2) and matches the CPU reference within tolerance (cross-backend harness); the fused pipeline is cache-hit on a second identical chain.\n**Exit gate:** cross-backend differential (fused GPU vs reference) + a no-readback trace assertion; gated on adapter presence; `just check` 0.\n**Refs:** plan.md §10.1, §12.3, §19 (M3). **Depends on:** wgpu scaffolding; Cross-backend harness; M2 graph simplification/fusion analysis [bn-28m].\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m3"],"parent":"bn-2ca","size":"l","title":"GPU pointwise fusion (readback-free GPU-resident subgraphs)"}	blake3:0FKkMkttoChzxLYAr8RlXyWCVQDEGdLMyLnUNmxOZQY
1782052837458235	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEz8AU		item.create	bn-3ka	{"description":"**What:** A wgpu implementation of paint.gaussian_splats@1 for large splat batches (plan.md §12.3 large splat batches). Honors the same params/semantics as the CPU reference (anisotropic sigma_x/sigma_y, angle, blend modes, opacity); benefits from the bbox-culling work (bn-2nr) for per-splat support.\n**Acceptance:** GPU splat batch matches the CPU reference within the op's declared tolerance (cross-backend harness) across small + large batches; deterministic given fixed dispatch ordering; degrades to CPU when no adapter.\n**Exit gate:** cross-backend differential (GPU splats vs reference) on small + large batches; gated on adapter presence; `just check` 0.\n**Refs:** plan.md §12.3; splat op [M0], culling [bn-2nr]. **Depends on:** wgpu scaffolding; Cross-backend harness; splat bbox culling [bn-2nr].\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m3"],"parent":"bn-2ca","size":"l","title":"GPU splat batch (paint.gaussian_splats on wgpu)"}	blake3:RhMXPk3vuJYQ9N9ogD0WjEA0QPNkn9tE6x_dMYAOyn4
1782052837582083	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEz8QU		item.create	bn-b4c	{"description":"**What:** wgpu separable filter kernels for filter.convolve / filter.gaussian_blur (plan.md §12.3 separable filters), with correct boundary handling matching the CPU reference at tile/texture edges.\n**Acceptance:** GPU separable filter matches the CPU reference within declared tolerance (cross-backend harness) across boundary modes and kernel sizes; no visible tile/texture seam; degrades to CPU when no adapter.\n**Exit gate:** cross-backend differential (GPU filter vs reference) across boundary modes; gated on adapter presence; `just check` 0.\n**Refs:** plan.md §12.3; M1 convolve/blur [bn-21l, bn-1vt], optimized separable Gaussian. **Depends on:** wgpu scaffolding; Cross-backend harness.\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m3"],"parent":"bn-2ca","size":"m","title":"GPU separable filters (convolve / Gaussian on wgpu)"}	blake3:O1XWoHPmqHXeg3yrVk5VAaqAEtR3J_9nthv8qK41GRU
1782052837702740	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEz8gU		item.create	bn-3q0	{"description":"**What:** Trace-level verification that a fully GPU-compatible chain incurs NO unplanned host readback (plan.md §19 M3 exit criterion 2) — readbacks happen only at declared materialization/export/assertion-on-host points. Surfaces readback events in the execution trace.\n**Acceptance:** a GPU-resident pointwise+filter+splat chain shows zero readbacks except at the declared export; inserting a host-side debug.materialize correctly introduces exactly one expected readback; the assertion is part of CI.\n**Exit gate:** `cargo test` readback-trace suite; gated on adapter presence; `just check` 0.\n**Refs:** plan.md §12.3, §19 (M3). **Depends on:** GPU pointwise fusion; GPU separable filters.\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m3"],"parent":"bn-2ca","size":"s","title":"No-unplanned-readback verification for GPU-compatible chains"}	blake3:FYGrZD1_2JhQRo3_0AGNcnG_XVNJusXQN2EsR_vxChM
1782052837824522	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEz8wU		item.create	bn-37k	{"description":"**What:** Close M3 (plan.md §19 M3 exit criteria) by wiring its four guarantees into a CI gate (ci/m3-gate.sh + `just m3-gate`, mirroring m2-gate): (1) every GPU op passes its tolerance contract against the CPU reference; (2) no unplanned readback in a fully GPU-compatible chain; (3) performance baselines are checked into CI artifacts; (4) GPU absence yields a clean fallback or explicit unsupported error.\n**Acceptance:** all four criteria pass in CI (GPU criteria gate on adapter presence but the fallback path is ALWAYS tested on GPU-less runners); M1/M1.5/M2 gates still green (no regression); perf + backend artifacts uploaded.\n**Exit gate:** CI \"M3 backends\" job green; `just m3-gate` 0; `just check` 0.\n**Refs:** plan.md §19 (M3), §12. **Depends on:** ALL M3 bones.\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m3"],"parent":"bn-2ca","size":"m","title":"M3 exit gate: GPU tolerance contracts, no-readback, perf baselines, clean fallback"}	blake3:HdWHi-t2-opGlrmjC0VSRjfAwc_jIxPoiqYv2AM9IgU
1782052851210753	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEz9AU		item.update	bn-2ca	{"field":"urgency","value":"default"}	blake3:C9G_DEP-SIXJ79ee4YV7MiLHXsckl4Tp2ZKPjuGSRtM
1782053069022328	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEz9QU		item.create	bn-mfw	{"description":"**What:** Multiscale frequency split (plan.md §1428 \"pyramids/frequency split\"; OP_CATALOG §9). Add a typed `Pyramid` resource (levels + downsample/phase convention, serde deny_unknown_fields) and three ops: `frequency.gaussian_pyramid@1` (image/field → Pyramid), `frequency.laplacian_split@1` (image → Pyramid), `frequency.recombine@1` (Pyramid → image, the inverse contract). Explicit phase/downsample convention (OP_CATALOG note).\n**Acceptance:** laplacian_split → recombine reconstructs the original within declared bounded tolerance (the §9 reconstruction test); gaussian_pyramid level sizes follow the stated convention; degenerate (1-level / odd-size) handled; Pyramid round-trips serde.\n**Exit gate:** `cargo xtask verify-op frequency.gaussian_pyramid@1 / laplacian_split@1 / recombine@1` + a split→recombine reconstruction differential; `just check` 0.\n**Refs:** plan.md §1428; OP_CATALOG §9; AGENT_VERIFICATION §3. **Depends on:** M1 convolution/resize [bn-21l, bn-2yy]; verify-op runner.\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m4"],"parent":"bn-21s","size":"l","title":"Pyramid resource + frequency.gaussian_pyramid / laplacian_split / recombine"}	blake3:Hc92SqERlXAkMouRnsPDe659krbjcO2Lya5kO8vfRsQ
1782053069144012	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEz9gU		item.create	bn-1fh	{"description":"**What:** Structure-tensor / orientation field (plan.md §1428; OP_CATALOG §8/§10.4). `filter.structure_tensor@1` (image/field → tensor via gradient scale + smoothing scale) and `field.orientation@1` (structure tensor → Field2 orientation + coherence) with an explicit eigenvector SIGN convention (OP_CATALOG note).\n**Acceptance:** orientation on a synthetic oriented grating recovers the known angle within tolerance; coherence ~1 on a clean edge, ~0 on isotropic noise; eigenvector sign convention is deterministic and documented; rotation covariance on a symmetric fixture.\n**Exit gate:** `cargo xtask verify-op filter.structure_tensor@1 / field.orientation@1` (analytic grating angle, coherence extremes, sign determinism); `just check` 0.\n**Refs:** plan.md §1428; OP_CATALOG §8, §10.4. **Depends on:** M1 convolution [bn-21l]; Field2 type [exists]; verify-op runner.\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m4"],"parent":"bn-21s","size":"m","title":"filter.structure_tensor@1 + field.orientation@1 (orientation/coherence field)"}	blake3:zptEbfTIDSNtE1CgtI1M6iuFYYtVOl0Kq3bmXtGoAEA
1782053069264038	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEz9wU		item.create	bn-1rt	{"description":"**What:** Edge-aware filters (plan.md §1428 \"guided or bilateral filtering\"; OP_CATALOG §8). `filter.guided@1` (input + guide → output via a local linear model) and `filter.bilateral@1` (image + spatial/range sigmas → image; expensive exact reference, approximation allowed later as a cpu.optimized/GPU variant). Both bounded-tier.\n**Acceptance:** guided filter with guide==input degrades to an edge-preserving smoother; a flat input is preserved (identity within tolerance); bilateral preserves a hard edge while smoothing a noisy flat region (measured); both match an independent reference impl on small fixtures; tolerance declared.\n**Exit gate:** `cargo xtask verify-op filter.guided@1 / filter.bilateral@1` (edge-preservation + flat-identity + reference differential); `just check` 0.\n**Refs:** plan.md §1428; OP_CATALOG §8. **Depends on:** M1 convolution [bn-21l]; verify-op runner.\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m4"],"parent":"bn-21s","size":"l","title":"filter.guided@1 + filter.bilateral@1 (edge-aware smoothing)"}	blake3:PR_SKW_3_kMCAsAggq4Hi5Mj6hBi9VrLdKi9LfBScV4
1782053069388356	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEz-AU		item.create	bn-15k	{"description":"**What:** The (screened-)Poisson solver core + ops (plan.md §1428 \"Poisson/screened-Poisson solver\"; OP_CATALOG §10.2). `repair.poisson_blend@1` (source/target/mask → candidate + report) and `repair.screened_poisson@1` (guidance/anchor/mask → candidate + report; explicit lambda semantics). Each EXPOSES convergence metrics (residual history) — a hard M4 exit criterion.\n**Acceptance:** seamless-clone of a gradient patch into a flat target has matching gradients inside the mask + continuous boundary (within tolerance); screened-Poisson with large lambda → approaches the anchor, small lambda → approaches pure Poisson; the report carries residual + iteration count; deterministic iteration ordering → bit-identical reruns on a fixed backend.\n**Exit gate:** `cargo xtask verify-op repair.poisson_blend@1 / repair.screened_poisson@1` (gradient-domain fixtures, lambda limits, convergence-metric presence, reproducible rerun); `just check` 0.\n**Refs:** plan.md §1428, §1441 (convergence metrics, deterministic ordering); OP_CATALOG §10.2. **Depends on:** M1 ops; mask infra [M1.5]; verify-op runner.\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m4"],"parent":"bn-21s","size":"xl","title":"Poisson / screened-Poisson solver + repair.poisson_blend@1 + repair.screened_poisson@1"}	blake3:_llUUtHY0FlF7LcLSFism03u63pdXHT7DAUdlazh13M
1782053069513256	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEz-QU		item.create	bn-2yl	{"description":"**What:** PatchMatch correspondence + patch fill (plan.md §1428; OP_CATALOG §10.2). Add a typed `PatchField` resource (per-pixel source offsets/NNF) and `repair.patch_field@1` (source/target/masks → PatchField) — PatchMatch, with an exact tiny brute-force backend as the differential oracle on small images. Reproducible tier (explicit seed + iteration/scan order).\n**Acceptance:** on a small image with a known repeated texture, the NNF maps hole pixels to correct matching patches (differential vs the brute-force oracle on tiny fixtures within the search budget); deterministic given a fixed seed + scan order (bit-identical reruns); PatchField round-trips serde.\n**Exit gate:** `cargo xtask verify-op repair.patch_field@1` (brute-force NNF differential, seeded determinism); `just check` 0.\n**Refs:** plan.md §1428, §1441; OP_CATALOG §10.2. **Depends on:** M1 ops; verify-op runner.\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m4"],"parent":"bn-21s","size":"l","title":"PatchField resource + repair.patch_field@1 (PatchMatch / patch fill)"}	blake3:wtoMbVTjOhq9vAhRurdWNXsAVsY1AhN4pWBEVxzd-JU
1782053069635395	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEz-gU		item.create	bn-1x5	{"description":"**What:** Deterministic procedural noise (plan.md §1428 \"procedural noise\"; OP_CATALOG §11). `field.noise@1` (extent + type + seed → field, HASH-based so it is reproducible and position-deterministic, not RNG-stateful) and `field.fbm@1` (extent + octaves + seed → field, with frequency normalization). Reproducible tier.\n**Acceptance:** noise is bit-identical across runs AND independent of tiling/evaluation order (hash-of-coordinate, not sequential RNG) — same value at (x,y) regardless of tile; fbm octave frequencies/amplitudes follow the documented normalization; changing the seed changes the field; value range bounded as declared.\n**Exit gate:** `cargo xtask verify-op field.noise@1 / field.fbm@1` (tiling-invariance, seed-sensitivity, range, fbm normalization); `just check` 0.\n**Refs:** plan.md §1428, §1444 (deterministic seed/ordering); OP_CATALOG §11. **Depends on:** Field types [exist]; verify-op runner.\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m4"],"parent":"bn-21s","size":"m","title":"field.noise@1 + field.fbm@1 (hash-based deterministic procedural noise)"}	blake3:tA4xqxa-tjzgyzY7RrJtdZ1WcoPtWqY5-MVqOsUIAew
1782053069756829	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEz-wU		item.create	bn-13f	{"description":"**What:** Domain warp (plan.md §1428 \"domain warp\"; OP_CATALOG §11). `field.domain_warp@1` (image/field + displacement field → same), reusing the M1 resampling contract (image.resize sampler/boundary policy) for the lookup. Bounded tier.\n**Acceptance:** a zero displacement is identity; a constant displacement equals an integer/fractional translate (matches image.crop/pad/resize translation); warp then inverse-warp round-trips within the resampler's tolerance; boundary policy honored; uses the declared sampler.\n**Exit gate:** `cargo xtask verify-op field.domain_warp@1` (zero-identity, constant-translate equivalence, round-trip, boundary); `just check` 0.\n**Refs:** plan.md §1428; OP_CATALOG §11. **Depends on:** M1 resize/resampling [bn-2yy]; field.noise (for warp fixtures); verify-op runner.\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m4"],"parent":"bn-21s","size":"m","title":"field.domain_warp@1 (displacement-field resampling warp)"}	blake3:HHpe0tTrYPS2vtjTKF27Q-zlX-wdTuCrr627xuaXCTI
1782053069876065	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEz_AU		item.create	bn-25w	{"description":"**What:** Reaction-diffusion (plan.md §1428; OP_CATALOG §11, P2). `field.reaction_diffusion@1` (initial fields + params → fields/report) — an explicit-step solver with documented stability bounds + step count. reproducible/bounded tier; report exposes step count + a stability/energy metric (convergence-metric exit criterion).\n**Acceptance:** a known Turing-pattern parameter set produces the expected qualitative pattern statistics on a seeded fixture within bounded tolerance; deterministic given seed + fixed step count (bit-identical reruns); stability guard rejects/clamps unstable step sizes; report carries step count + metric.\n**Exit gate:** `cargo xtask verify-op field.reaction_diffusion@1` (seeded determinism, stability guard, metric presence); `just check` 0.\n**Refs:** plan.md §1428, §1444; OP_CATALOG §11. **Depends on:** field.noise (init); verify-op runner.\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m4"],"parent":"bn-21s","size":"m","title":"field.reaction_diffusion@1 (stable stepped solver, P2)"}	blake3:Wp22g25SkFpvUqOtGaTrpO1YgCH9q8nns2mbn8zMNU4
1782053069999999	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEz_QU		item.create	bn-3m3	{"description":"**What:** The contract-driven local optimizer (plan.md §1428 final deliverable; ALIEN_OPS). A generic iterative local optimizer that drives a candidate toward satisfying an op/assertion contract (e.g. minimizing a declared residual/objective under a mask), exposing convergence metrics and obeying deterministic seed/ordering rules (the two governing M4 exit criteria). Bounded/reproducible tier.\n**Acceptance:** on a synthetic objective with a known minimum, the optimizer converges to it within tolerance and the report records the residual trajectory + stopping reason; deterministic given seed + fixed schedule (bit-identical reruns); a max-iteration / no-progress stop is honored (no runaway).\n**Exit gate:** `cargo test` optimizer suite (known-minimum convergence, metric trajectory, seeded determinism, stop rules); `just check` 0.\n**Refs:** plan.md §1428, §1441/§1444; ALIEN_OPS. **Depends on:** OpContract/assertion infra [M0/M2]; verify-op runner.\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m4"],"parent":"bn-21s","size":"l","title":"Contract-driven local optimizer (iterative, convergence-metered, deterministic)"}	blake3:0EoRL1tnSoKJ0FSUTMjVEnS2UntJRMePc_Chup8JDP8
1782053070124226	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEz_gU		item.create	bn-3n9	{"description":"**What:** Texture-preservation analysis (OP_CATALOG §13/§14; supports the M4 \"known/bounded synthetic fixtures\" exit criterion). `analyze.frequency_energy@1` (image/field + bands → report) and `assert.frequency_preserved@1` (images + mask/bands → report/fail) for verifying a touch-up did not destroy band energy outside the edit.\n**Acceptance:** frequency_energy reports per-band energy matching an analytic multi-frequency fixture; assert.frequency_preserved passes when bands are preserved and FAILS (with a band-energy delta) when a region is over-blurred; band/window policy explicit.\n**Exit gate:** `cargo xtask verify-op analyze.frequency_energy@1 / assert.frequency_preserved@1`; `just check` 0.\n**Refs:** OP_CATALOG §13, §14. **Depends on:** Pyramid resource + frequency ops; verify-op runner.\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m4"],"parent":"bn-21s","size":"m","title":"analyze.frequency_energy@1 + assert.frequency_preserved@1 (texture-preservation metrics)"}	blake3:1G0Y4fUnVEA9yO_Sa_ABjkN6xaWRQolJzapXJptt1Yc
1782053070247353	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEz_wU		item.create	bn-2bg	{"description":"**What:** P2 STRETCH (OP_CATALOG §9): an internal typed complex-spectrum resource + `frequency.fft2@1` (field/image → spectrum), `frequency.ifft2@1` (spectrum → field/image), `frequency.bandpass@1` (image/field + response → same, explicit boundary/window policy). Optional within M4 — file but lowest priority.\n**Acceptance:** fft2 → ifft2 round-trips within numerical tolerance; a known sinusoid produces the expected spectral peak; bandpass attenuates the declared band; boundary/window policy documented; bounded tier with declared tolerance.\n**Exit gate:** `cargo xtask verify-op frequency.fft2@1 / ifft2@1 / bandpass@1` (round-trip, known-spectrum, band attenuation); `just check` 0.\n**Refs:** OP_CATALOG §9. **Depends on:** verify-op runner. (Lowest M4 priority — defer if M4 scope tightens.)\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m4"],"parent":"bn-21s","size":"m","title":"frequency.fft2@1 + ifft2@1 + bandpass@1 (typed complex spectrum, P2 stretch)"}	blake3:ZhE7Ndc3zU6b46rh_te8pnXePIec0ujved_cWfqvMVU
1782053070371899	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzgAY		item.create	bn-3jk	{"description":"**What:** Close M4 (plan.md §1441 exit criteria) via a CI gate (ci/m4-gate.sh + `just m4-gate`): (1) each SOLVER (Poisson, screened-Poisson, reaction-diffusion, PatchMatch, local optimizer) exposes convergence metrics in its report; (2) each ITERATIVE op has deterministic seed/ordering rules (bit-identical reruns asserted); (3) each op has a synthetic fixture with a known or bounded outcome (verify-op passes); (4) performance + memory scale are characterized (artifacts uploaded). NOTE: the M4 \"EDT + SDF mask algebra\" deliverable already shipped in M1.5 (bn-9oi) — this gate covers the remaining M4 ops only.\n**Acceptance:** all four criteria pass in CI across the M4 ops; M1/M1.5/M2/M3 gates still green; perf/memory artifacts uploaded.\n**Exit gate:** CI \"M4 classical magic\" job green; `just m4-gate` 0; `just check` 0.\n**Refs:** plan.md §1428–§1446 (M4); M1.5 [bn-9oi] (EDT/SDF already done). **Depends on:** ALL M4 op bones.\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m4"],"parent":"bn-21s","size":"m","title":"M4 exit gate: solver convergence metrics, deterministic seeds, bounded fixtures, perf/memory"}	blake3:zkxCwKRFC_R90-fJe1aus56IIFeWOY0o1lxEBMyaALc
